title: pepper biscuits
directions: First mix together the flour, salt, pepper and fennel seed. Next, make a hole in the center of mixture.
Put water and dry yeast; dissolve yeast well, then mix all the mixture together. Cover mixture with a cloth and let mixture rise for 1 hour.
Cut dough into pieces and roll to form biscuits.
Drop dough into boiling water until they rise to the top.
Remove and place on cookie sheet; bake for 1/2 hour at 450°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend well into greased casserole dish.

title: dee's concord grape pie
directions: To prepare Concord grapes with seeds, remove and save skins from grapes (pinch grapes at end opposite stem; fruit pops out).

title: peach cobbler 1
directions: Spread pie filling in 2-quart baking dish. Combine dry cake mix, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut in butter. Crumble over pie filling. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top is golden brown. Serve warm, plain or with ice cream.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions, radishes and cucumber in salad size pieces in bowl with oil.
Add vinegar to taste and 1/2 bottle Salad Supreme until salad turns red.
Add cooked noodles and mix well.
Chill.
Serve cold.
Tastes better when made 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Save 1 cup cake mix.

title: old fashioned broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook onions and celery until tender-crisp.
Add other ingredients except cheese.
Spoon into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Melt.

title: mini-popovers
directions: Beat eggs
slightly
in medium-sized bowl.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the
milk,	flour
and
salt.
Add remaining milk and 1 tablespoon butter.
Beat
just
until	smooth.
Gently stir in almonds.
Pour batter
into
well-greased
3/4-inch muffin cups, filling each
half full (about scant tablespoon).
Bake 10 minutes	at 450°.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake 20 to 25
minutes. Make small slit in side of each popover to let steam escape. Serve hot with butter.

title: cajun rice dinner
directions: Cook sausage for 2 minutes in large skillet.
Add onion and cook and stir until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low heat about 20 minutes until liquid is absorbed. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie(yum yum!!)
directions: Cream the peanut butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Crumble Reese's cups into mixture. Scoop into shell.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Just before serving, drizzle chocolate syrup over individual servings.

title: mandarin chicken with noodles
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick coating.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Stir-fry chicken, half at a time, about 3 minutes or until no longer pink; remove.
Break up the Oriental noodles (set flavor packet aside).
Add noodles, zucchini, celery, garlic and 1 cup of water to skillet.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until noodles and vegetables are tender.
Stir in chicken, the flavor packet contents, sweet and sour sauce and peanuts; heat through.
Top each serving with orange sections.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blue ribbon sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and dice sweet potatoes.
Place in saucepan with enough cold water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
If using canned sweet potatoes drain and mash.
Using an electric mixer, beat potatoes until smooth and set aside.
Beat eggs, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and ginger, mixing well.
Add sweet potatoes, beating well to mix.
Slowly add evaporated milk, beating until smooth.
Pour custard into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake for 40 minutes or until center is set.
Cool and chill.
Whip and spread cream on top of pie.

title: no knead refrigerator dough
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup;
level off.
In a large mixing bowl combine 2 cups
flour,
yeast,
sugar
and salt. Add hot water, margarine and eggs.
Mix
at
low
speed until moistened;
beat 2 minutes at medium
speed.
Stir
in 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour to form
stiff
dough.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours
or
up to 4 days. Shape into 24 dinner rolls.
Bake until tests done.

title: indiana baked beans
directions: Soak the beans overnight in a large kettle of water.
Simmer them for about 1 hour in the water in which they were soaked.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix 3 ingredients.
Roll dough into small balls and press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen 1-inch cookies.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Heat brown sugar, whipping cream and oil until smooth.
Shake biscuits in a sugar-cinnamon mix until well coated.
Arrange biscuits in a Bundt pan and pour caramel mixture over the top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Flip onto serving dish.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli, cheese and soup. Stir until cheese is melted.
Add rice, salt and pepper to taste. Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sauteed noodles and mushrooms
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Drain.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add noodles, parsley, salt, garlic and cheese.
Heat through and serve.
Serves 4.

title: aunt helen's rice pudding
directions: Put rice, salt and cold water in saucepan and cook approximately 20 minutes.
When cooked, put in buttered casserole (3 quart).
Add 6 beaten eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla raisins, nutmeg and butter.
Set casserole in pan of hot water.
Place in a 350° oven.
Cook approximately 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Blend together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cut in margarine (like coarse meal).
Add raisins, caraway seed, buttermilk or sour cream and egg.
Stir until blended. Knead on a board about 5 minutes.
Make 2 balls.
Place in 2 greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Flatten to fill pan.
Cut a deep "x" in the top.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate italian cake
directions: Beat egg whites at high speed with electric mixer until stiff peak forms. Set aside. Beat butter and shortening until creamy. Gradually add sugar beating well. Add egg yolks one at a time, beating until blended after each addition. Combine flour, cocoa, and soda, to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk beginning and ending with flour mixture. Beat at low speed until blended after each addition. Stir in coconut, chopped pecans and vanilla. Fold in egg whites. Pour batter in 3 greased and floured 8 inch round cake pans. Bake at 325 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Cool completely. Spread chocolate cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. This is a version of the Italian cream cake.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Melt butter.
Cream butter and sugar, add egg then add yeast.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Bake in greased muffin pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Unused portion may be kept in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: beef tips
directions: Place
beef
in
casserole
dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, lemon pepper and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Combine 2 soups and small amount water to rinse cans.
Pour over beef; cover with foil.
Bake
at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Butter a 10 x 7 x 3-inch baking dish.
Place buttered bread in bottom.
Sprinkle raisins over bread.
Scald milk.
Beat eggs slightly and add sugar and vanilla to eggs.
Pour milk on eggs, gradually beating at same time. Pour this mixture over bread in dish. Bake in basin of water.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar when it is done.
Bake in a 425° oven for 35 minutes.

title: sweet dill chips
directions: Drain pickles and slice; layer with onion back into jar or several smaller jars.
Boil sugar, water and vinegar for 3 minutes.
Pour over to cover and put lids on tightly.
Let sit on counter for 3 days, then refrigerate.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a new flowerpot and silk flowers.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and oil.
In a cup, combine soda and buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture.
Place dough on a floured board.
Knead until dough is smooth.
Roll out in 1/2-inch thickness.
Flour top of glass (size of glass determines size of biscuits).
Place on greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Remove with metal spatula or knife.
Serve with butter.

title: ehu molokai sweet potatoes limu cold soup
directions: Thoroughly clean fish bones by running tap water over bones for 5 minutes.
Place bones in large soup pot with rest of ingredients.
Add 3 quarts of cold water, cover and bring to boil. Skim the surface to remove scum, simmer for 15 minutes.
Strain stock through a fine sieve.
Yield: 2 quarts.

title: spinach and mushroom casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray a 1-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Saute mushrooms in stock in a large skillet.
Combine mushrooms and remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish. Cover and bake 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients to this mixture and blend well.
Divide and shape into 2 rolls, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in waxed paper, place on plate and chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Cut thin slices of chilled dough with sharp knife and place on cookie sheet which has been rubbed with shortening.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
Watch closely, they will burn easily.
Leave in pan until cool, they tear up easily.
When cool, put in plastic bag to keep fresh and crisp.

title: easy hamburger pie
directions: Saute meat, onion and bell pepper; drain.
Mix all ingredients except cornbread with meat.
Top with cornbread (made according to package).
Bake according to cornbread recipe for 20 to 30 minutes until bread is done.

title: quick and easy tater casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pack ground beef into bottom of medium size baking dish, then spread on cream of mushroom soup.
Now, layer Tater Tots.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with Cheddar cheese and let cheese melt.

title: cured leg of lamb(fenalar)
directions: Rub leg with salt, sugar and saltpetre mixture.
Place on wooden board.
Leave for 3 days, turning frequently.
Do not let meat dry out too much.
Hang in cool, dry place to age.
Wipe off any mold that may form.
Meat is ready for use after 6 to 8 months. Slice thin and serve without cooking.
Meat may be used after 2 months, but must be cooked.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Dissolve the yeast into the cup of lukewarm water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of the sugar.
Stir and let stand about 5 minutes.
Pour the scalded milk into a mixing bowl; let cool.
Cream the shortening thoroughly.
Add remaining sugar and the salt gradually; cream again.
When yeast is soft, add it to the lukewarm milk.
Stir in 3 cups of the flour; beat smooth.
Blend in the creamed mixture, the beaten eggs and the spice (if used). Stir in remaining flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Knead well, working in only enough flour to avoid stickiness.
Bake, after raising twice the size, for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: best-ever fruitcake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Put dry ingredients in sifter. Alternately add an egg at a time, with part of the sifted dry ingredients, till all is combined, then add the wiskey.
Chop the cherries and pineapple (not too small) and rub a little flour on them so they don't float to the top.
Add the fruit and nuts.
Put into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Wrap well.
Keeps for weeks.

title: gumdrop nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Cut gumdrops in half.
Place them in a mixing bowl.
Put walnuts in a plastic bag and crush them with a rolling pin.
Put crushed nuts in bowl with gumdrops.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Stir until well mixed (set aside).

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and egg. Sift together remaining ingredients and beat well. Roll batter into balls about the size of pecans. Roll each ball in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheets 2-inches apart. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: spinach spread dip
directions: Stir ingredients together and refrigerate before serving. Great served with crackers.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Cut coconut rolls in half. Roll apples and coconut in dough.
Put in pan.
Dot with butter. Add sugar and juice together.
Pour over rolls.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green beans parmesan
directions: Cook and drain beans.
Sprinkle with cheese, Equal, garlic and pepper and toss until beans are coated.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Let your child crush several graham crackers in a plastic bag, using a rolling pin. Mix enough to stick ingredients together.
Roll into balls.

title: pizza lovers casserole
directions: In skillet, brown onion and ground beef.
Drain.
Add soups and pizza sauce to beef mixture.
Stir and cook until heated. Cook noodles according to package directions, reducing cooking time by 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: cajun cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Separate frozen roll dough into pieces (each cloverleaf makes 3 pieces).
Combine dry pudding mix with brown sugar and pecans. Melt butter.
Place pieces of frozen roll dough in a well buttered Bundt pan.
Pour melted butter over frozen dough and sprinkle with pudding mixture.
Leave cake pan out overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert on serving plate to serve.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: At medium heat in large frying pan, saute until light brown the garlic in olive oil and remove garlic.
Saute until transparent the onion and remove.
Dip eggplant in egg mixture and lightly in crumbs.
Saute until tender, adding more olive oil as needed.
Likewise, cook the zucchini but do not overcook.
Layer eggplant and zucchini with tomato sauce, onion and cheese, topping with the cheese.
If ingredients are still warm, bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until topping is browning.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of large rectangular casserole dish with whole crackers.
Add chicken, then celery and onion.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top. Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle 1 cup shredded cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in small casserole except the chow mein noodles.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Add chow mein noodles on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: sour cream porcupines
directions: Combine beef, rice, paprika, salt and onion.
Shape into 16 to 20 balls.
Brown meat balls in hot fat.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Drain fat from skillet.
Combine in skillet, water, cube, Worcestershire sauce and soup.
Stir until blended.
Add sour cream and pour mixture over meat balls.
Cover; refrigerate or freeze.
Bake uncovered in moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes or 1 1/2 hours if frozen.
Serve with Chinese noodles sprinkled on top.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar, flour and salt.
Mix well with beater.
Add chocolate syrup and instant pudding mix (dry); beat until well mixed.
Pour into 1 quart chocolate milk and mix until blended well.
Put this mixture into freezing container and finish filling container with chocolate milk.
Stir well with long spoon; freeze.

title: tonda's homemade chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Salt and pepper.
Drain fat.
Blend tomatoes in blender.
Add tomatoes, beans and chili powder. Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Mix shortening and margarine together.
Add sugar and salt; beat until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add half of the flour and half of the milk, then, after thoroughly blending, add the other flour and milk, as well as the vanilla.
Beat thoroughly at a high speed.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan; bake for approximately 2 hours at 325°.

title: rice pudding
directions: To the rice add the sugar, butter, milk and slightly beaten eggs. Add raisins and vanilla. Put in deep dish and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt.
Add cherries.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Add dots of butter.
Top crust. Cover edge well.
Bake in hot oven about 15 minutes, then reduce heat and bake until done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Toss biscuits in 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Put into a greased Bundt pan.
Melt 3/4 cup margarine and 1 cup sugar until it boils. Drizzle over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and invert out of pan.

title: racheal's baked italian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased baking dish. Pour dressing evenly over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: granny's muscadine or grape jelly
directions: Cook grapes or	muscadines
in	water,	stirring
often until tender
and juicy.	Strain juice.
Using Sure-Jell, make jelly as the directions on Sure-Jell package.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts. Press into the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Mix well the cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip and the vanilla.
Spread on top of cooled crust. Mix pudding mix and milk; spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Last, top with the rest of the Cool Whip; sprinkle nuts on top if desired.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Bring butter, brown sugar, powdered sugar and vanilla ice cream to a boil.
Add rum and boiling water.
Add 3 tablespoon of mixture to a mug.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Cool slightly.
Mix eggs, sugar and butter together.
Beat
well.
Add
cornmeal.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and coconut.
Bake in a 325° oven for approximately 40 minutes. Cool before slicing.

title: my buddy's pizza casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown the ground beef, onion, green pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Drain excess grease.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles until soft in boiling water; drain. Combine meat sauce and noodles in a large casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese rice
directions: Cook the rice.
Add the soup and cheese.
Place this mixture in a greased casserole dish. Cover the top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until the crumbs are browned.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Stir together egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, sifted with salt and baking soda.
Add walnuts.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes in well-greased 8-inch square pan at 350°.
Cookies should be soft when taken from oven; cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 25.

title: mock sausage patties
directions: Mix together beef, lemon juice and rind, bread crumbs, salt, sage, ginger and beef stock or bouillon.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Form into 8 patties about 3/4-inch thick.
Brush a heavy skillet with oil and set over heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Put in the sausage patties and cook 7 to 8 minutes on each side.
Serve hot.

title: quick carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in large bowl.
Blend together in blender oil and eggs.
Gradually add a handful at a time of carrot pieces to the mixture, blending after each addition.
Blend until the carrots are fine in size.
There should be about 5 cups of mixture when finished.
Add flavoring and pecans or raisins, if desired.
Pour in with dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes.
Also can be baked in muffin tins.
Enjoy as a sweet bread or ice with cream cheese icing.

title: to freeze melons
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan.
Stir over heat until sugar is dissolved; let boil 5 minutes without stirring. Cover pan and cool.
Add lemon juice for flavor and to prevent discoloration.
Refrigerate, use as needed.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallows, well.
Place in a well-greased baking dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Top with marshmallows and continue to bake until they are light brown.

title: ranch salad
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces and place in bottom of large dish. Layer tomato, onion, beans, Doritos and cheese.
Pour whole bottle of creamy Italian dressing over all.

title: parks fruit cake
directions: Soak nuts and fruits in wine overnight.
Then mix.
Pour into 1 large or 2 medium tube cake pans.
Cook at 250°
for 5 hours with water in oven. Makes 10 pound cake.

title: pickled three bean salad
directions: Wash beans. Remove strings and trim ends from green and wax beans. Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Shell lima beans. Combine beans, celery, onion and pepper in large saucepot. Cover with boiling water. Cook 7 to 8 minutes. Drain. Bring sugar, vinegar, water, mustard seed, celery seed and salt to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Pack hot beans in hot jars.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients. Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Crumble and stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cheddar and chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute mushrooms in 4 tablespoons butter until well browned.
Add heavy cream, cheese, salt and pepper. Stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and place in freezer until mixture becomes solid.
Remove from freezer and slice into 12 equal pieces.

title: pumpkin crumb
directions: Mix together pumpkin, salt, milk, cinnamon, eggs and sugar. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until middle is set.

title: emily's salad
directions: Drain the oranges well, then mix in milk and juice.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into the crust.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours. Can also be used as a dessert.
Very good served with pork.

title: low-fat meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together thoroughly. Add ketchup as desired. Place in a greased pan. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and cook 30 more minutes or until brown.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Fry breast strips in deep fat.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
In large pan, boil water and bouillon cubes.
Stir in sugar and cornstarch.
Add oyster sauce and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Top with green onions and cashews.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with sliced apples or any other desired fruit.

title: chocolate fudge(glenda lindstrom, dublin, va)
directions: Warm cream and chocolate until chocolate is melted, then add sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Put lid on for a minute or two (this is to melt any sugar crystals that might have formed on side of pan).
Cook to 240° on candy thermometer at low altitudes*.
Remove from heat and pour on greased marble or formica slab.
Put butter and vanilla in the center.
Cook until candy is lukewarm in the center.
Knead with a spatula (or a wide putty knife kept for this purpose) until it loses its gloss.
Quickly add the nuts, then press into a buttered pan.
Cut into squares after the candy has cooled.

title: tuna and rice
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet (medium-high heat).
Add onion.
Cook until tender, not browned.
Stir in vegetables, milk, soup and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Stir in tuna, rice and parsley. Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Add almonds, if desired.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add shortening, milk and bananas.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat.
Pour into 2 greased and waxed paper lined 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all vegetables in a large pot, cover with water and simmer until veggies are tender.

title: irish rag cake
directions: Mix this all together.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° until done.
Test with a toothpick inserted into the center.

title: moma's blueberry pies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, pour into 2 graham cracker pie crust. Spread cool whip on top of cream cheese filling. Then spread blueberry pie filling on top of cool whip. Refrigerate, serve.

title: dad's favorite sugar cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on a floured board.
Cut out, using a 3-inch cookie cutter.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: lo-fat soup
directions: In a big pot, put 1/4 pot of water; add the 3 cubes of beef. Add onions, cabbage, meat, corn, tomatoes, frozen vegetables and salt and pepper to taste.
Fill up with water and stir good.
Cook on low 45 to 50 minutes.
(Any frozen vegetables can be substituted.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add slightly beaten eggs. Sift together flour and baking soda.
Blend with mixture, scrape side of bowl.
Add pecans.
Blend thoroughly.
Add hot water to mashed bananas and mix well.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into each well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: master mix chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add 2/3 cup of milk or water and beat for 2 minutes.
Add rest of milk or water, eggs and vanilla and beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12 or two 8-inch pans.
Bake at 275° for 25 minutes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Combine moist ingredients in a bowl except gumdrops.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients with moist ingredients.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Mix in gumdrops.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cooking Time: 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 35-minute gumbo
directions: On a large plate, using a fork, stir 1/2 teaspoon paprika, ground red pepper and black pepper until well-combined; set aside. In a large pot, bring chicken broth, salt and 4 cups of water to a boil.
Add okra and corn; boil 10 to 12 minutes, until okra is tender and liquid thickens slightly.
Stir in remaining teaspoon paprika.

title: onion pocket bread
directions: Assemble doughmaker with small bowl.
Heat water to 120°.
In small bowl, place 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, salt and sugar.
Add water and oil; mix with doughmaker at setting #12 for 3 minutes. Gradually add enough remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead with doughmaker about 4 minutes until smooth and satiny.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Beat eggs, add milk, butter, vinegar and vanilla.
Blend both mixtures; pour into unbaked pie shell and bake about 45 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: lemonade
directions: Dissolve 1 cup of sugar in 1 cup of cold water and 1 cup lemon juice.
Add 4 cups cold water.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon peel.

title: mints
directions: Knead until like pieces of pie dough.
Add more sugar, if needed.
Roll in marble size.
Roll in sugar.
Press in mold and place on wax paper until dry.
Can be kept indefinitely in refrigerator or frozen.

title: no-knead onion bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine i cup of the flour, the sugar and the yeast.
In a small sauce pan over med.-high heat, heat soup and butter until very warm (120 to 130 degrees).
With mixer at low speed, gradually pour soup mixture into ingredients, mixing well. At medium speed, beat 3 minutes or until smooth.
Add egg, cheese and 1 cup of the flour, beat 2 minutes more.
With spoon stir in enough remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hrs.
Grease 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Stir down batter turn into prepared casserole.
Cover, let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Brush with water and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake 50 minutes or until bread sounds hollow with tapped finger.
Remove from pan; cool on wire rack before slicing.

title: spinach or broccoli quiche
directions: Thaw shells.
Cook spinach or broccoli in microwave.
Drain. Saute onion in bacon grease.
Mix everything in bowl.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Should be dry and firm when done.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order:

title: southern baked pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Wash 6 pork chops very well and lay in baking pan.
Sprinkle onion and bell pepper on top of pork chops. Mix flour and water well; sprinkle over the pork chops.
Cook in oven for 45 minutes.

title: viennese coffee (diet)
directions: Pour coffee and Alba '66 into cup and gently stir until completely dissolved.
Top with a dollop of whipped topping. Sprinkle with a few grains of cinnamon, if you like.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mash bananas.
In large mixing bowl, mix eggs, sugar, Eagle Brand, half and half, bananas and vanilla.
Pour into freezer and add enough milk to fill to line indicated on freezer.
Yield: 1 gallon freezer.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: First mix together flour, salt, dry mustard and garlic powder. Dip pork chops in mixture, then brown in oil.
Place browned pork chops in crock-pot and pour chicken and rice soup over pork chops. Cook low all day.
Serve over rice.

title: turkey chili
directions: In a large, heavy pot, brown turkey; pour off any excess fat. Add onions, green pepper and garlic; cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans, water, tomatoes, tomato paste, chili powder, oregano, cumin and red pepper.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with cornbread.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine all and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Trim off crusts of bread; cut into 6 strips.
Put on cookie sheet; bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Cook oil and peanut butter on low heat until blended.
Dip the strips into the mixture; lift with fork and roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet to dry.

title: chinese salad
directions: Boil 1	cup
of
vinegar
and
1 cup of sugar together. Pour over vegetables and cover.	Chill overnight.
It's great served with sausage casserole.

title: boiled cake
directions: Boil raisins, sugar, water, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and lard or fat.
Boil 15 minutes.
Remove from stove and cool.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to boiled mixture and bake at 375°.

title: party cheese ring
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over cold water in saucepan.
Place over low heat.
Stir constantly until dissolved, 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Gradually add gelatine.
Stir until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir to mix.
Pour into a 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Serve with crackers.
Also nice in containers for gifts.

title: simple fruit cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Pour batter in greased and floured cake pan.
Drain the fruit and pour over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: poultry main dishes
directions: Place chicken breast in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Spread mushrooms on top.
Cook, covered, in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with egg noodles.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Melt butter in with meat.
Stir in 2 cups of water and dry onion soup.
Let come to boil.
Blend sour cream and flour together and stir in with meat mixture.
Let cook a few more minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: icing for sugar cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add 1/2 of powdered sugar slowly.
Add vanilla, salt and cream of tartar.
Add remaining powdered sugar.
Spread on cookies.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
(I usually put in half box and then sweeten to taste with rest of the box.
It usually doesn't take all of box.)
Add Cool Whip, then add water a little at a time, enough to make it thin enough to pour into baked crust. Top with strawberries and glaze.
Refrigerate.
Yummy, yummy.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Process half of the berries and half of the orange, then do second half.
Add sugar to desired sweetness.
Refrigerate.

title: quick skillet chicken parmesan
directions: In medium skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil. Add chicken and cook 10 minutes or until browned; set chicken aside. Pour off fat. Add spaghetti sauce. Heat to a boil. Return chicken to pan. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Top chicken with Mozzarella cheese. Serve with spaghetti.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cream cheese.
Beat with electric mixer at low speed until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, sugar, vanilla and nuts (if desired).
Add 7-Up.
Stir, when partially set, to keep nuts from coming to the top.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Cook for 45 minutes on 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender.
Drain and mash well.
Add cheese and other ingredients.
Pour into casserole, and top with buttered bread crumbs.
(I use Italian style bread crumbs.)
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kipper pate
directions: Melt a knob of butter in frying pan.
Add Kipper fillets and fry gently for 10 minutes or until fish is soft and will flake with a fork.
Remove from pan, leave to cool, then remove any skin and large bones.
Put Kipper fillets in bowl and mash with a fork. With a wooden spoon, beat the remaining ingredients.
Add black pepper to taste; beat until pate is quite smooth.
Spoon into container.

title: plum pudding
directions: Put milk with chopped fruit in double boiler.

When cooked slightly, add cocoa or chocolate, which has been melted and mixed with part of the sugar and a little milk to make a smooth paste. Pour cold water in bowl and sprinkle gelatine on top of water.
Add to hot chocolate mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar and salt and stir thoroughly.
Remove from fire; cool, and when mixture begins to thicken, add nuts and vanilla.
Lastly, fold in whites of eggs, beaten very stiff.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onion.
Layer in a greased casserole dish. Mix soups together and thin with 1 can of milk. Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into large, well-greased casserole dish.
Reserve enough corn bread stuffing mix to sprinkle.
Top lightly.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add dry ingredients; drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Take a glass, dip bottom in oil then dip in sugar and press cookies out.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw crust and top.
In medium saucepan, whisk together cornstarch and apple juice until well blended.
Add spices and salt.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir mixture until thick.
Pour over apples.
Dot with butter.
Cut slits in top of crust.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry tomato salad
directions: Place tomatoes in a shallow bowl.
In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the oil, vinegar, parsley, basil, oregano, salt and sugar.
Shake well.
Pour over tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Place meat in heavy skillet.
Cook over medium heat until it loses all its color.
Drain off fat.
Stir in next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Dip half the tortillas in melted butter.
Arrange on bottom and sides of a large casserole.
Spoon in meat mixture.
Do not disarrange tortillas.
Spread chopped chilies over mixture with all but 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover with remaining tortillas and add sauce, smoothing over whole surface.
Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle casserole with reserved cheese before baking in a 325° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: baked apples in lemon sauce
directions: Core apples and place in a dish; cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are crisp, as they will have 10 more minutes baking time when custard is added.
Beat egg until light and fluffy; beat in sugar, milk, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Add the margarine.
Drain the hot juice from the apples (if any) and stir in custard.
Pour custard over apples and continue baking, until custard is set, about 10 minutes.
Serve hot with custard sauce over apples.

title: curried chicken soup
directions: In Dutch oven, combine chicken, water, 1 onion (quartered), celery, garlic and 1 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour until tender. Remove chicken to cool.
Discard skin, bones, leaving meat in large chunks. Set aside. Strain broth. Save five cups.

title: seafood stuffing(old mill restaurant recipe)
directions: Melt butter, add to Ritz crackers.
Add sherry and mix together.
Add onion rings and crab meat.
Mix together with your hands and pat on fish.

title: white wash for chicken coop
directions: Fill pail with water.
Throw in salt.
Keep adding lime, stirring until you get paint-like mixture.
Paint coop every year and
hose it down between paintings.
The lime helps control pests.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion. Drain fat. Combine and add all other ingredients, except beans. Stir well. Add beans. Stir well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: my sister's best whole wheat pancakes
directions: Beat egg until fluffy.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Cook as usual.

title: cookies: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt butter or margarine and the unsweetened chocolate in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Blend sugar into melted chocolate and the eggs, one at a time. Beat for 1 minute.
Add flour, baking powder, salt (sifted) and walnuts (optional).
Mix well.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Shape into balls, using one teaspoon of dough for each.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cold soups - summer favorites
directions: Blend together chicken soup, chicken broth, yogurt or sour cream, onion, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and curry powder in blender or Cuisinart with one of the following:
cucumber, zucchini or summer squash.
Chill.
Top with dollop of sour cream or yogurt. Sprinkle with dill.

title: egg souffle
directions: Beat eggs in mixer.
Blend flour, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese, margarine and everything else except tomato.
Cook in greased pan.
Put tomato on top and cook for 40 minutes or until brown.
Let settle out of oven for about 5 minutes.
Great for brunch.
Makes 15 or more servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in large skillet.
Drain off grease.
Lightly drain tomatoes.
Cut up tomatoes and add meat with taco seasoning and seasoned salt.
Stir well.
In separate bowl, combine egg and cottage cheese.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased baking dish at 350° until brown on top.

title: corn-cheese casserole
directions: Mix corn, 1 cup cheese and onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except remaining cheese.
Mix well.
Pour mixture in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add remaining cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain potatoes and put in bowl.
Add oleo, brown sugar, salt and pepper and mash.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Cut 6 marshmallows into quarters and mix into potatoes.
(Can use mini marshmallows whole.)
Put mixture in greased casserole and cover top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: christmas aroma
directions: Peel fruits.
Bring all ingredients to a boil in a kettle and let simmer as long as needed to scent the house.
May be used more than once, just save the juice.

title: chocolate angel bar pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars and water in microwave or double boiler. Stir in vanilla; let cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie shell; chill well.
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients into a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil; stir until moistened.
Do not use electric mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and banana.
Spoon into three 9-inch round cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mock dried peaches
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Freeze in containers.
Use your favorite recipe for fried pies.

title: spanish rice
directions: Preheat frypan at
Add
shortening
and rice and stir until rice is lightly browned.
Mix remaining ingredients together;
stir.
Cook covered at 225° for 30 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: buttermilk scone hearts
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt until thoroughly blended.
Using a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Stir in dates and orange peel.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture; add buttermilk all at once.
Stir mixture with a fork until dough cleans the sides of the bowl.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Pour Cool Whip, lemonade mix and Eagle Brand milk into bowl. Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: corn relish
directions: Bring all ingredients together except corn and bring to a boil.
Add corn and cook 20 minutes.
Before canning, add 1/4 tablespoon turmeric and 1 tablespoon celery seed.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Blend together Crisco and sugar, creaming well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend in the dry ingredients gradually.
Mix. Add pecans, dates and maraschino cherries; mix.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls into 2 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Toss lightly to coat.
Form into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Top each with 1/4 maraschino cherry.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread in an 11 x 15-inch oblong pan.
Combine in a bowl the next 3 ingredients.
Spread on top of potato mixture.
Crush 2 cups potato chips or corn flakes and put on top of mixture. Dot with 1/2 stick margarine. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 425° to 450° 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy punch recipe
directions: Mix sugar, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice with a can of water form the pineapple juice.
Put in refrigerator until needed.
Add ginger ale last, when it is needed.
Can use an ice ring in it or sherbet.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Place in a greased 8-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: creamy salad
directions: Mix well together.
When ready to serve, slice bananas into it.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
Cook onion and celery over medium heat until translucent, about 20 minutes.
Add green onions and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in Creole seasoning.
Add shrimp and cook, covered, stirring 3 or 4 times, until just done, about 5 minutes.
Serve over white rice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and chill for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Use 1/2 watermelon as a serving bowl.
This makes a great table piece at showers and summer parties.

title: sweet potato or pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 400° for 15 minutes and turn oven down to 350°. Cook 40 to 50 minutes more, until knife comes out clean in the center.

title: apple pie
directions: Trim crusts of bread.
Cut each slice of bread into five pieces.
Place apples into a baking dish.
Lay sliced bread over apples.
Mix sugar, flour, egg and vanilla.
Spoon over bread. Bake at 375° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: naanee's pea soup
directions: Mince the onions.
Slice carrots and celery.
Mix all the ingredients with the salt and pepper according to taste.
Boil, then simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dilly-bacon cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, add crumbled bacon along with dill. Mix in
separate bowl, the liquid ingredients and stir into cornmeal mixture until just combined.
Spoon into greased 8 x 8-inch pan or cornstick mold.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Par-boil macaroni.
Brown hamburger, salt & pepper.
Add onions, green peppers and mushrooms.
Pour spaghetti sauce over meat and vegetables.
Add 1 1/2 c. cheese and pepperoni.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 c. cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry swirl cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Dot top of cheesecake with preserves.
Cut through batter with table knife several times for marble effect. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Garnish with Cool Whip and raspberries.
Will serve 10 to 12.

title: dewberry coffee cake
directions: Cream
oleo, sugar, vanilla and eggs together.
Fold in flour. Pour
batter
into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan; spread
dewberries on batter and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: saucy baked new potatoes
directions: Halve or quarter scrubbed potatoes.
Put into an oven-proof casserole dish.
Coat potatoes with fat free salad dressing. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° covered for 45 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix all together to form dough ball. Roll out on wax paper. Take about a cup of peanut butter (more or less, if desired). Spread on mix. Roll up in a log.
Set in refrigerator for 10 minutes to chill. Take out and cut into slices.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix together; pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate about 12 hours.

title: bean and sausage soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, cook sausage until lightly browned. Remove sausage.
Add carrot, celery, onion and thyme; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, gradually stir in water.
Add pepper and sausage.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon into a large mixing bowl.
Make well in center.
Combine eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans.
Add sifted ingredients, stirring until well combined.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.

title: no egg potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes. Let them cool and then cube them into bite size pieces. Mix other ingredients and add to the potatoes and let cool in the refrigerator.

title: baked tomato pasta
directions: Cut tomatoes in half lengthwise; set cut side up in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Mix garlic with 1/3 cup parsley and 2 tablespoons olive oil; pat mixture over cut side of tomatoes.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons of olive oil over tomatoes.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip on bottom of container.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together.
Spread sour cream mixture over top. Sprinkle remaining ingredients over top.

title: mushroom florentine
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Saute cleaned (or drained) sliced mushrooms in melted butter.
Place spinach in a 6 x 9-inch shallow casserole.
Top with salt, chopped onion and garlic.
Add butter and mushrooms.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
May be made and refrigerated before baking. Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add oil, eggs and carrots; beat 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.
Use two 9-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Thoroughly sift together into bowl the flour and white corn meal. Stir in sugar and salt; rub in the butter. Beat the eggs thoroughly and add to the mixture with the milk. Lastly, add in the baking powder and mix with a spoon to a stiff batter; pour into well-greased pans and bake quickly in a preheated oven at 425° or 450° for 25 minutes or until top is golden.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Sift dry ingredients again.
Melt oleo; remove from heat and add brown sugar.
Mix well.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, beaten, and vanilla and blend well.

title: cheese soup
directions: Add boiling water to potatoes, celery, onion, salt, pepper, bouillon cube and parsley flakes.
Cover and cook until tender. Blend flour with small amount of milk.
Stir into vegetables.
Add balance of 2 cups milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: shake and bake chicken coating
directions: Combine ingredients.
Store in Ziploc bag or airtight container.

title: coconut almond carrot ring
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat sugar and oil at medium speed of mixer until well mixed.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition. Stir in carrots, nuts, raisins and 2/3 cup of coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch Bundt pan or 6 cup ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish on cooling rack.
Frost with cream cheese frosting and cover with coconut.

title: brazil nut fruit cake
directions: Put nuts,
dates
and
cherries
in a large bowl.
Sift flour, sugar
and baking powder and salt over nuts and fruits. Mix with hands
until
nuts and fruits are coated.
Beat eggs until	foamy. Add
vanilla.
Stir
all
together.
Turn	into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in slow 200° to 250° oven for 1 hour. Cool before removing.

title: brijolli
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, seasonings and egg.
Add enough oil to mixture to make it hold together when squeezed.
Cut meat into 4 x 4-inch pieces.
Fill each meat square with stuffing mixture.
Roll up and tie with string.
Brown meat in frying pan with small amount of oil.
Place meat rolls in Ragu sauce; cook for at least 2 hours, covered.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, mashed bananas, milk and nuts. Add alternately to the flour mixture. When well blended, pour into a greased bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frosted valentine cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, oats, extracts and salt.
Mix well.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a 3-inch heart-shaped cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While cookies are warm, spread melted chocolate on top.
Cool.

title: gooey bars
directions: Combine honey and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Press into an ungreased 9 X 9 X 2 inch pan.
Chill for one hour.
Cut into bars.

title: chocolate eclaire dessert
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Mix Cool Whip with pudding.
Line bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Cover with layer of pudding mixture.
Cover with another layer of crackers, layer of pudding, and final layer of crackers.
Heat opened icing can in microwave about 20 seconds, then spread over crackers. Chill overnight.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix. Bake. Let set until warm. With a sharp fork, pierce holes in entire cake. Pour condensed milk over cake, then the can of cream of coconut juice. Let absorb and cool. Spread cool whip and top with coconut.

title: lime yogurt salad
directions: Drain pears.
Dissolve one jello package in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix and pour into 8 x 8-inch dish and let thicken.
Place pears on top, when jello is firm, then dissolve second jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool slightly and add 8 ounces yogurt.
Pour over first layer and chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut in 9 squares.

title: fried green beans
directions: Put onion and bacon in frying pan.
Cook until good and brown. Drain green beans.
Add to onions and bacon.
Cook on medium-high for about 5 minutes, then simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Mix sugar and mayonnaise.
Layer in order:
lettuce, celery, onion, peas, mayonnaise, cheese and bacon.
Do not mix. Refrigerate.
Cut through to bottom when serving.

title: frozen dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl thoroughly
mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved dry yeast.
Combine water, milk and margarine over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°); margarine does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel and let rest 20 minutes.

title: rising crust pie
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Stir flour and milk into a batter.
When margarine melts, pour into pan.
Mix fruit with sugar to suit your taste.
Heat until sugar dissolves, then pour over crust in pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until brown.
Crust will rise over fruit.

title: meat loaf with cranberry
directions: Add all ingredients to hamburger.

title: beef stew
directions: Cube beef; saute in small amount of fat.
Slice onions and saute in fat.
Place beef, onions, carrots, tomatoes, basil, pepper and water into large covered pot.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add potatoes the last 45 minutes.

title: veal cutlets
directions: Roll veal in flour, dip in egg and roll in cracker crumbs. Heat a small amount of oil in skillet; brown veal on both sides. Remove from skillet and put in baking dish.
Put 1 tablespoon tomato sauce on each veal cutlet.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Combine butter and sugars and mix until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour.
Add chocolate chips. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Peanut butter chips may also be substituted for chocolate chips.
Cookie dough may be stored in covered container in refrigerator and baked as needed.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Combine oleo, sugars and eggs; mix well. Add fruit cocktail, nuts (or coconut), 2 cups flour, baking powder, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and flavoring.
Mix together with mixer.
After these are all mixed, add 2 more cups flour, stir into batter. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
In a large casserole, layer potatoes, soup mixture and sausage.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° about 1 hour.

title: overnight breakfast
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and salt.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Sift dry ingredients and cut shortening into dry mixture.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Knead on floured board. Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pans and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
(Batter can be stored in refrigerator for several days until ready to use, if desired.)

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and make into balls.
Flatten.
Dip into chocolate.

title: baked stew
directions: Bake at 275° for 5 hours, covered.
Do not take cover off.

title: apricot upside-down cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Arrange apricot halves, cut side up, over sugar. Sprinkle with coconut and almonds.
Mix together next 3 ingredients.
Blend in margarine with pastry blender or fork. Beat eggs and add to milk, then stir into dry mixture.
Blend and pour over fruit into pan.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Remove cake from pan by placing serving plate over cake pan and carefully invert.
Decorate top with maraschino cherries.
For easier handling, bake cake in spring-form pan.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift cornmeal, flour, salt, sugar and baking powder together in a bowl.
Beat the eggs in a small dish, then add them to the cornmeal mixture.
Add the melted butter and mayonnaise, then blend all ingredients thoroughly.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in milk until smooth.
Then add vanilla flavoring and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust and place in refrigerator.
Chill for 2 hours and add fruit topping or leave plain, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Cook squash until tender and drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream, soup and onion.
Pour melted butter on dressing.
Mix well.
Alternate layers of squash, soup and dressing in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Can freeze ahead.

title: green beans and mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter.
Add green beans.
Cook until hot.

title: pudding pie
directions: Mix the pudding as directed, but use 2 cups of milk.
Let stand a few minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a 13 x 9-inch dish, put whole crackers down.
Put half of pudding mixture, another layer of crackers, then the rest of pudding mixture and end with crackers.
Pour the cherry pie filling on top.
Refrigerate around 2 hours before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over pie filling.
Top with coconut.
Sprinkle nuts over coconut. Spread cake mix over top.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Soften margarine and mix with crushed graham crackers.
Press in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Layer 4 cups strawberries.
Mix water and cornstarch in pan and cook until clear.
Add strawberry Jell-O and remove from heat.
Pour over strawberries.
Set and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate or shallow ovenproof dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with sliced green onions and chopped tomatoes before serving (if desired).
Serve with tortilla chips, crackers or assorted cocktail bread slices.
Makes 2 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in buttered casserole dish.

title: macaroni-shrimp salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill; add paprika to serve.

title: mock country fried steak
directions: Mix egg, milk, 1/2 cup crackers, onion, chili powder, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape into 6 patties about 1/2-inch thick.
Coat each with remaining crackers.
Cook in 1/2-inch oil over medium heat about 8 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and melted butter and then add juice and grated rind from lemons.
Pour in partially baked pie crust. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean when inserted in pie.

title: apple salad
directions: Prepare jello with 3 tablespoons sugar, salt and water.
When this starts to thicken, add apples, bananas and crushed pineapple. In saucepan, cook together pineapple juice, 1/2 cup sugar, egg and flour.
Let cool, then add 1 package of Dream Whip prepared according to directions.
Spread on top of jello mixture and sprinkle with nuts.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: mock wild rice stuffing
directions: Melt
butter
in large saucepan.
Add rice, onion, mushrooms, celery,
celery leaves, salt, pepper and spices.
Saute over medium heat, stirring constantly, 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned;
add
water,
mix
just enough to moisten all rice, bring
quickly
to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer
2 minutes
fluffing
rice
gently once or twice with a fork. Remove from heat.
Add pecans and mix lightly with fork. Spoon stuffing
into
poultry.
Do not pack tightly.
Roast at once. Makes
enough
for 4 to 5 pound chicken, or use pheasant or quail or dove.

title: crock-pot camp stew
directions: *Or combination you desire.

title: nutty rum balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, pecans and rum into a paste. Add sugar. Let stand in refrigerator for an hour. Pinch off small pieces and roll into small balls. May be rolled a day before serving. Keep in a well covered dish.

title: chocolate dip balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls and put on wax paper.

title: celery deluxe
directions: Put celery and butter in 2-quart casserole, cover and microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add peas, stir, cook on High 5 more minutes, stirring once.
Stir in drained olives, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on High 2 more minutes.
Serve in a pretty white bowl.

title: seafood boil
directions: In a very large saucepan with a removable wire basket, heat water, crab boil, salt, Tabasco sauce and lemon to boiling.
Add onions, artichokes, carrots and potatoes; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Carefully remove vegetables.

title: raisin bars
directions: Boil raisins and water together until water is absorbed. Cream the oleo and sugar together.
Add oatmeal, flour, soda and vanilla.
Pat 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the egg yolks, 1 3/4 cups sugar, cornstarch, salt and vinegar.
Cook until thick; add raisins and cool and spread over crust.
Put remaining crumbs over filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
In separate bowl, combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in shredded zucchini.
Add mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack and cool completely.
Makes 2 loaves.
Freezes well.

title: pineapple yellow cake
directions: Bake yellow cake as directed.
While hot, poke holes in the cake with a meat fork; pour can of crushed pineapple (with juice) onto cake.
Let cake cool.

title: spinach bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan and heat enough to melt shortening.
Cool to lukewarm and add dill and onion. Measure warm water and yeast into large bowl and allow yeast to start to work.
Add milk mixture and soda with flour; beat until smooth.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Put into a greased bowl, cover and let rise until almost double in size.
(Before dough is ready to roll out, fry bacon and chop real fine.)
Roll out dough on flat surface.

title: tropical salad
directions: Combine apple and banana; sprinkle with orange juice and toss lightly.
Add celery, coconut, raisins and walnuts; stir in enough mayonnaise to moisten. Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Top with almonds and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add all ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half of mixture into mold.
Let chill one hour.
Spread sour cream over gelatin mold, spoon remaining mixture over top and chill.

title: pineapple-pie
directions: Mix pineapple and instant vanilla pudding together until thick.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip and pour in baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: popcorn snowmen
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter.
Remove from heat and add popcorn a little at a time.
Let cool a minute.
With buttered hands, shape mixture into balls for body and head (tennis ball and golf ball sizes).
Use raisins, etc. for eyes, nose, mouth and buttons.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water, Karo and peanuts until light brown in color (almost 10 minutes).
Stir in soda.
Pour on greased cookie sheet to cool.
Break apart.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain and serve.

title: easy casserole(ham or turkey or chicken)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix soups, 1 cup of milk, meat and onion powder in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put beef in large soup pot.
Cook meat (do not brown) until grey.
Stir to break up meat into small pieces.
Combine onions, tomatoes, juice from tomatoes, tomato sauce, potatoes and frozen mixed veggies.
Add garlic powder, salt and chili powder, mint, black pepper, parsley flakes, water and cooked macaroni.
Bring to boil then simmer and cook approximately 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: potato and vegetable salad
directions: Peel and slice the potatoes while warm and lightly salt before completely cool.

title: raisin pie
directions: In a saucepan, stir together sugar and flour.
Add water and mix well.
Stir in raisins, salt and cinnamon.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Pour into a pastry lined pie plate. Top with lattice crust or cover with top crust and cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken, put in casserole dish sprayed with Pam, and pour the dressing over top.
Bake in 425 degree oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: soap balls(non-edible)
directions: Place in 1-quart mixing bowl the Ivory Snow.
Add hot liquid. Mix well.
It will be like paste.
Shape into balls or roll out on pastry sheet and cut out shapes.
It is important to let the soap balls and/or shapes dry 24 to 48 hours.

title: mouse salad
directions: Put pear halves core side down on top of lettuce leaves.
Put 2 whole cloves on each for eyes (narrow end of pear).
One raisin for the nose and a carrot curl for the tail. For the ears, cut a marshmallow into slices with kitchen scissors.
Attach to pear with wooden toothpicks.
Serves 4.

title: white clam sauce for vermicelli
directions: Saute garlic in oil, mashing to extract juice.
Add clam juice, salt, pepper and oregano; simmer 5 minutes.
Add clams with juice.
Stir in well and cook uncovered, about 8 to 10 minutes so liquid will reduce a little.
Mix in parsley and onion tops.
Toss half of sauce with vermicelli and top with the rest of the sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Serves 4.
(Can be doubled.)

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into muffin tins lined with paper muffin cups.
Freezer until firm.
Store in plastic bag. Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: jeannine's better than bottled bleu cheese dressing
directions: Crumble Bleu cheese and mix in sour cream.
Add wine vinegar, olive oil and mayonnaise and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add salt, pepper, dry mustard, seasoned salt, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce to taste.
Blend well.
Chill. Best if made the night before you intend to use as it has chance to season.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: joyce's peach cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and peaches.
Melt butter in a very deep dish. Pour in peaches and sugar.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon; save drippings.
Set bacon aside and crumble. Dice potatoes.
Combine with onion and bacon.
In drippings, add salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour over potato mixture, stirring slightly to blend.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple mint supreme
directions: In small pan bring juice to a boil and stir in jello.
Cool. Cream the cream cheese with sugar.
Blend in jello mixture.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until thick, not set.
Chill milk and peppermint extract until ice crystals form.
Beat until thick. Fold into pineapple-cheese mixture.
Spoon over baked crust. Refrigerate overnight for best results.
(If time is essential, 4 or 5 hours will be enough.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and pour into a greased baking dish.

title: coconut crunch delight
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a medium size saucepan over moderate heat. Remove from heat. Beat in sugar gradually with a wooden spoon until thoroughly combined. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition; stir in vanilla. Stir in flour until thoroughly combined. Stir in 1 cup of the walnuts. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 pan. Combine remaining 1/2 cup walnuts with chocolate chips; sprinkle over top of cookie mixture, pressing down lightly. Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed with fingertips. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Cut into bars.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Mix the cake mix as directed on box.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 32 to 37 minutes.
Put the pineapple in a saucepan. Boil 3 minutes. While the cake is still hot, punch holes in cake and pour on the cake.
Let soak in.

title: chocolate sure punch with ice cream islands
directions: Place chocolate flavored mix in a large bowl.
Stir in milk. Beat with rotary beater until blended.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add scoops of ice cream.
Pour carbonated water and let chill.
Yields 48 servings.

title: easy punch(for 40 to 50 people)
directions: Using food coloring the color of the sherbet for your color scheme.

title: maple walnut cups(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl with hand, knead flour, butter or margarine and sugar until well blended.
Divide dough into 16 pieces.
Press dough pieces into bottoms and up sides of 16 (1 3/4-inch) muffin pan cups.
In a 1-quart saucepan over low heat, melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Remove from heat; stir in corn syrup, maple extract, egg and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts evenly into each pastry cup; spoon syrup mixture on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until crust is lightly browned and toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Store in refrigerator.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces. Fry in butter and oil the onion, chopped into small pieces and rosemary.
Saute and then add white wine.
Cook for 5 minutes with wine.
Make sure bacon is cooked well.
Cool spaghetti for minimum time on package (al dente). Combine eggs, cheese and parsley in a large bowl; beat with fork. Add spaghetti; mix well.
Add bacon mixture; mix well and serve.

title: fruitcake squares
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine, then pour into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, tilting pan to spread butter evenly. Sprinkle crushed vanilla wafers evenly over butter in pan. Arrange nuts, dates and candied fruits evenly over the crumb mixture and press down gently.
Combine sweetened condensed milk and the 1/4 cup milk; pour evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set. Cool, then cut into squares.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix Jell-O in bowl according to directions.
When it begins to set, add cooled rice and pineapple.
Mix in well and fold in whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: great grandma lizzie's orange-sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can of onions; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered; top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer, uncovered. Serves 8 to 10.

title: monster cookies
directions: In a very large mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugars together.
Beat in well the eggs and vanilla.
Blend in the peanut butter.
Stir in the flour, soda and salt.
With a strong wooden spoon, mix in oatmeal, M&M's and chocolate chips. Use an ice cream scoop to put on pans.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Yields a lot of large cookies!

title: creole corn
directions: Fry onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: caramels
directions: In large pan combine first 4 ingredients but only 1 can milk. Bring to boil for 15 minutes.
Add second can of milk.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add last can of milk.
Use candy thermometer and cook until it reaches 250°.
Add vanilla.
Stir and pour into greased pans.
(I use one 9 x 13-inch and one 9 x 9-inch pan.)
Let sit overnight.
Cut and wrap.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets in large amount of water until tender.
Remove hot water and cool down before peeling beets.
Slice beets in whatever shape you prefer.
Cover beets in solution mixture as given until completely covered.
Bring to a boil; fill sterilized jars and seal.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Mix Ro-Tel and cheeses in crock-pot.
Simmer until melted. Add sausage and stir. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: guacamole and chips
directions: In a blender, process all ingredients at slow speed until mixed.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yields 2 cups.

title: whiskey wieners
directions: Bring bourbon to boil.
Reduce heat and add brown sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook over low heat until the mixture thickens; add sliced wieners (cocktail wieners can be used).
Cook until ready to serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil
together	the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter into hot syrup.	Mix together.
Add rolled oats
and
vanilla.	Drop
on
waxed
paper	and set in refrigerator for a few minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Put potatoes and onions into a greased 9x13 pan.
Mix sour cream, butter, and soup and spread over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Melt 1 stick butter and mix with crushed cornflakes.
Put on top of casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Place first 3 ingredients into bowl and let set for 2 hours; drain well.
Pour last 3 ingredients over drained cukes and freeze.
Defrost as needed.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a shallow baking pan, skin side up. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake 1 1/4 hours, basting every 15 minutes or so until chicken is tender and nicely browned.

title: bacon, lettuce and tomato dip
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl and gradually stir in dressing. Mix well. Remove seed from tomato and dice. Chop bacon, celery and onion. Add tomato, bacon, celery, onion and sugar to cream cheese mixture. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours to allow flavors to blend. Line bowl with lettuce leaves. Fill with dip and garnish with chopped tomato. Serve with Wheat Thins or Triscuits.

title: (like) colonel sanders chicken
directions: Wet chicken and shake up thoroughly in a plastic bag, coating chicken with the above mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes. Tastes like original Colonel Sanders chicken.

title: sunday meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the tomato sauce.
Put the meat mixture into greased loaf pan.
Top with tomato sauce, seasoned with your favorite herbs (oregano, basil, thyme, etc.) Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Pour in milk and mix well.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with butter.
Melt 2 teaspoons shortening in pan.
Put biscuits in hot shortening and turn over. Bake at 410° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: garlic roasted chicken
directions: In large roasting pan; place chicken, potatoes and garlic. Pour butter over all and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes, basting frequently.
Heat honey; baste over chicken. Spoon pan juices over potatoes and garlic.
Bake 20 minutes or until tender.
Serve soft roasted garlic, several to each person, cut through skin and spread pulp over chicken and potatoes. Serves 6.

title: steamed shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp.
Mix all ingredients and place on stove.
Bring to a boil.
Place shrimp in boiling mixture and steam 20 minutes.

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk. Add flour slowly. Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chocolate jumbos
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients well.
In separate bowl mix next 5 ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; mix well. Batter will be sticky.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll on floured board.
Cut with donut cutter to desired size.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on middle rack.
Frost with Vanilla Icing after cool.

title: finger salad
directions: Unroll dough on cookie sheet.
Pat down to cover.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, dry dressing mix and enough mayonnaise to make spreading consistency. Spread over crust.
Sprinkle vegetables over.
Top with grated cheese.
Chill.
Cut into desired size squares to serve.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix in bowl.
Add meat.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Turn meat occasionally.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Beat ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Add 1 teaspoon to boiling cup of water and shot of rum.
Store in covered container in freezer.

title: water chestnuts wrapped in bacon
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: oven tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cheese and 1 cup of the corn flakes in a baking dish and fluff so it sits lightly in the dish.
Top with the flakes and the cheese and bake until bubbly in a 450° oven, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves about 6.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add to mixture and mix well.
Heat to boiling point milk and butter, add all at once to mixture.
Beat well.
