Do not add any more flour to batter, it is very thin.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven and spread with blended mixture of melted butter, brown sugar and cream. (Optional:
Walnuts and/or coconut.)
Place under broiler until topping bubbles up.
Remove to cool.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients with milk alternately.
Add nuts and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and melted butter.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour peaches (juice and all) over batter. Do not stir. Bake at 350° until done. Batter will rise to top. Delicious served hot with ice cream.

title: breakfast or brunch casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain well.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Tear bread in pieces and sprinkle over margarine. Sprinkle drained sausage, cooked well done, over bread crumbs. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs with half and half and salt; pour over mixture.
Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with blueberry muffins and cantaloupe.

title: cappuccino
directions: In saucepan, add Caffe' Espresso and 1/2 cup milk per serving; bring to boiling point, then add sugar to taste and blend.
Pour into cup and sprinkle cinnamon and chocolate.
Ahh, good.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Season the chopped meat to your own taste and form small meatballs.
Add the meatballs to the cooking sauce and simmer 3/4 hour or until meatballs are thoroughly cooked.
If necessary, add water.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Line corn chips in dish.
Brown meat and drain.
Add seasoning and 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce.
Mix 1/2 cup tomato sauce with refried beans.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Pour bean mixture over meat; sprinkle with chips and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: elegant eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and soak in salt water overnight in refrigerator (this is important).
Soak bread crumbs in evaporated milk and whole milk.
Saute chopped vegetables in oleo until tender.
Boil eggplant until nearly tender and drain well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and place into a preheated 400° oven and bake until golden brown.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed and mix. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 250° until knife comes out clean, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fried bean patties
directions: Mash up drained beans or peas. Add other ingredients (add more flour if needed). Spoon into hot shortening with big rounded over tablespoon of mixture. Fry until golden brown on both sides. Delicious!

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In
13 x 9-inch pan, mix everything but crackers together and pour into pan.
Put crackers on top of chicken mixture.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Recipe doubles well.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix uncooked oatmeal, melted margarine, sifted flour and brown sugar until crumbly.
Press half the crumbs into greased 10-inch baking pan.
Cover with diced rhubarb.
Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cut in squares and serve warm with whipped cream of ice cream.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon in a large plastic Baggie.
Shake the cut up biscuits in the cinnamon mixture.
Put the sugar coated biscuits into a Bundt pan.
Melt the butter and brown sugar together.
Pour over the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Turn over onto plate.
Eat warm and pick apart with fingers to eat.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces. Season with salt and pepper. Melt shortening in a heavy iron pot.
Fry chicken until brown; remove from pot; set aside.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Use 1/2 less water.
Let cool.
Clean and devein shrimp.
Cut peppers and onions in chunk size.
Slice mushrooms and cut olives in half.
Saute shrimp in olive oil until pink.
Set aside.
Stir-fry vegetables; set aside.

title: streusel topped pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Combine pumpkin, Eagle Brand, egg, 3/4 tsp. cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350 degrees. Combine sugar, flour and remaining cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle mixture over pie.
Bake 40 minutes or until set.
Top with whipped cream if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt chocolate bars in syrup over low heat.
Cool.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cooled chocolate, then flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix soup with one can water; set aside.
Combine rice, hamburger meat, onion, salt, pepper and 4 tablespoon soup mixture; mix well.
Form into balls.
Place in casserole; cover with remaining soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake another 15 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients with creamed margarine and brown sugar, egg whites, applesauce and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Drop with teaspoon on baking sheet, greased.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are slightly brown.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Shape ground round into 6 to 8 patties. In a large iron skillet with oil, brown the patties and remove from skillet. Add to the oil in pan the flour. Slowly brown. Add the tomato juice, vinegar, ground cloves, sugar, salt and onions. Allow to come to a boil; return the patties. Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stars and stripes torte
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions, using two greased 9-inch round baking pans.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks to cool completely.
In a small mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding mix on low speed for 2 minutes. Beat in extract.
Cover and refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Split each cake into 2 horizontal layers.
Place bottom layer on a cake plate; spread with raspberry pie filling. Top with second cake layer; spread with 1 2/3 cups of pudding mixture.
Top with third cake layer and spread with blueberry pie filling.
Top with remaining cake layer and pudding mixture.
If desired, place blueberries around top edge of cake and form a star with blueberries and raspberries.
Yield:
10 to 14 servings.

title: sweet-sour beef stew
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Add next 6 ingredients, 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water; add to beef mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Serve over noodles sprinkled with poppy seed.
Garnish with carrot curls and parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Great served with grilled hamburgers.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Stir together.
May add more milk if needed.
Mixture will be lumpy.
May add cut up apples, blueberries or raspberries, as desired.
Pour pancakes on hot, lightly greased griddle.
Takes a little longer than regular pancakes to cook.
Watch for brown edges and bubbly middle before turning.

title: homemade face paint
directions: Stir together the cornstarch and cold cream until well blended.
Add water and stir.
Add food coloring, one drop at a time, until you get the desired color.
Experiment with the colors by adding more drops of the same color for a darker paint or by adding a different color to create a new shade.
Three drops of blue and one drop of green food color will create turquoise. Two drops of yellow and one drop of red blends into orange.
Two drops of blue and one drop of red will make violet.
Paint designs on faces with a small paintbrush; remove with soap and water.
The face paint may be stored in covered containers.
Yogurt containers are a good size.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange fluff fruit dip
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Gently beat in sour cream.
Fold in orange peel and orange juice.
Chill.
In center of serving tray, set a small bowl of pudding.
Arrange fruit around the bowl.
To keep fruit bright, dip in lemon juice, mixed with a little water.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sherbet; mix well. When partially set, add oranges and fold in Cool Whip.

title: barley-vegetable soup
directions: Place barley, chicken stock, onion quarters, carrot thirds, celery slices, thyme and bay leaf in a large soup pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for about 1 hour or until barley is tender.
Add sliced carrots, celery, zucchini and chopped onion and cook until tender.
Add spinach a few minutes before serving.
Makes nine 1-cup servings.
Per serving:
100 total calories; trace sat-fat calories.

title: elegant scalloped potatoes(ready in one hour or less.)
directions: Scrub and pierce potatoes; place on a microwave safe plate. Microwave on high for 15-20 minutes or until tender. Cool slightly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add syrup and coffee. Beat eggs well, then add vanilla and rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for about 45 minutes.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Blend meal
with
salt
in
mixing
bowl.
Pour boiling water over mixture while stirring until it becomes consistency of dough. Form
dough
into patties and brown on each side in hot bacon drippings.
Yield:
6 small servings.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, and salt, set aside.
In a saucepan, put margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour-sugar mixture.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk, and vanilla to mixture.
Bake in greased and floured deep cookie sheet (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inches).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken on rice
directions: Blend soup and milk; reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Stir together remaining soup mixture, mushrooms (with liquid), rice and 1/2 the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken pieces on rice mixture.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle on the remaining onion soup mix.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: party meatballs
directions: Blend together and make into small balls.
Place in a baking pan; bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Place into prepared Hot Dunky Sauce.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt over low heat 1/2 stick butter and add 6 ounces chocolate chips. Pour over top of peanut butter mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: nabisco crush
directions: Beat eggs, butter and sugar together.
Spread in layers in order given; with 1/2 the Nabisco wafers on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the filling and top with the rest of the Nabisco wafers.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Stir milk into the egg. Add to dry ingredients and mix well.

title: layer fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg yolks (beaten), then add milk and juice, flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in last.
Divide into 2 parts.
To one part, add 2 cups nuts and two 8 ounce packages of cherries.
To the other part, add 1 teaspoon of allspice, 1 box dates (chopped) and 8 ounces of raisins.
Bake in layer pans (4).
Put together alternate layers with filling.

title: rosemary cream-cheese eggs
directions: Beat eggs, cream and salt together in a small bowl.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased, hot skillet, sprinkle rosemary on top, and scramble until slightly runny.
Add cream cheese in dollops, and fold in gently.
Garnish with rosemary sprig, if desired, and serve hot.
Makes 2 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruits, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemonade and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thick.
Blend in whipped topping and fold in fruit.
Freeze until firm.

title: anise bread
directions: Scald milk and water together; add Crisco and anise seeds and let cool to room temperature.
Mix flour and sugar in large bowl - make a well, when cool pour above liquid into well.
Add yeast and sugar to warm water and let stand till frothy - almost double in volume - pour into well.
Add all the eggs and mix well.
Knead until not sticky adding more flour as needed.
Divide into 8 parts and put into greased 8 inch x 4 inch baking pans and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° until nicely browned (about 30 minutes).
Brush left over egg whites on top of loaves to make them shinny.

title: cream cheese roll
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet; press together cracks.

title: clam chowder
directions: Use a heavy pot. Fry fatback and saute onion.
Add liquid, tomatoes, potatoes and seasoning.
Cook until potatoes are done, then add clams and continue to cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 8.
(For larger amounts, increase proportionately.)

title: candy suckers
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Heat on medium until temperature gauge is at soft ball.
Remove from flame and add coloring and flavor of choice (just 2 or 3 drops of flavor oil). Stir and pour into molds with sucker sticks and there you are: suckers.
Makes 21.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together in large bowl.
In separate bowl, mix together vinegar, sugar and oil.
Pour liquid mixture over vegetables and stir.
Chill until serving.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add beans and let simmer.
Cut lettuce into bite-size pieces and add onion, tomatoes, cheese and Doritos. Mix well.
Add dressing; mix well.
Serve warm.

title: spiced beets
directions: Mix juice from beets, sugar, vinegar and allspice.
Bring to a boil.
Mix water and cornstarch together.
Add to mixture.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Add beets; simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: dip for fresh fruit
directions: Mix ingredients and blend.
Peel and slice any kind of fruit you like.
Place on platter.
Place dip in center and serve.

title: lemon crunch cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Put 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Put 1/2 of this crumb mixture over batter.
Add the rest of the batter and cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake according to cake mix directions.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350°.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour. (Usually little longer than an hour.) Add bacon bits last 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix melted oleo and crackers together; set aside until later. Mix the next four ingredients together and set aside until later. Mix the next three items together and layer on bottom of the casserole dish.
Top with soup mixture.
Cover with cracker mix. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(Can be made ahead and frozen.)

title: sauteed chicken breasts and crab meat el pearson
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts and roll in flour, shaking off excess.
Heat oil in skillet and brown chicken on both sides. Remove chicken and pour off excess oil.

title: gourmet mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add margarine, cream cheese, sour cream, milk and egg.
Whip until smooth.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika for color and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
If taken from refrigerator, extend baking time to 50 minutes.
Potatoes are very fluffy when served.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Add water to pineapple juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir in lemon juice.
Stir mixture into gelatin mixture.
Chill until consistency of egg whites.
Add cranberries, oranges and nuts to mixture; mix well.
Refrigerate until set.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Dredge tomato slices in cornmeal and flour.
Pour oil to depth of 1/4-inch into a large heavy skillet.
Fry tomato slices, a few at a time, in hot oil over medium heat for 2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, enchilada sauce, onions and black olives. Line pan with 3/4 of chips and pour mix on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Put remaining chips on top.
Pour broth over and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pan-fried pork chops
directions: Wash chops; pat dry and season with salt and pepper. In large skillet, heat oil. Flour chops and sear in the oil. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes per side to brown. Remove and pat dry on paper towels. Put the chops back in the skillet and add the chopped onions and chopped garlic to pot with 1/4 cup water. Put lid on the pot and steam chops approximately 20 minutes.

title: shrimp salad for a crowd
directions: Put the ingredients in bowl and mix together.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator, covered.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Layer meat, potatoes and soup.

title: mother chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together. Add eggs yolks, milk, vanilla and flour. Bake 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough 2-inches larger than inverted 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Ease into plate and flute edges.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Pound steak 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in serving pieces.
Blend egg and milk.
Dip meat into egg mixture, then into cracker crumbs. Slowly brown meat in hot oil, turning once.
Cover and cook over low heat 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: spicy rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage, cumin and garlic powder, stirring often.
Drain.
Add onions and green peppers; saute until crisp-tender.
Dissolve bouillon in water; add to skillet.
Stir in jalapenos, rice and rice seasoning packet; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes or until the water is absorbed.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandmother's polish bread
directions: Warm milk in a 6-quart pot.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter; cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into small bowl, crumble in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add to milk mixture, stir in eggs and vanilla, gradually add flour.
Knead dough in pot about 30 minutes until it no longer sticks to your hands, then add raisins and knead into the dough.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and divide dough in half.
Shape into loaves and place in two greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch bread pans.
Combine 1 egg with 2 tablespoon water; brush the bread with this mixture and let rise uncovered in a warm place until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until done.

title: one-dish meal with beef
directions: Saute beef and onions in shortening.
Add rice; brown.
Add remaining ingredients; cook to steaming point.
Cover on top of range at low heat for 30 minutes or in electric skillet.

title: berry jams
directions: *Can use blackberry, blueberry, bosenberry, dewberry, gooseberry, raspberry or loganberry.

title: nibblers
directions: Cream margarine and cheese together.
Combine flour and onion mix.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make small rolls as for refrigerator cookies.
Slice and bake for about 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Will slice better if chilled for 3 or 4 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 8 ounces hot water and chill.
Cut fruit into small pieces and mix with chopped pecans and miniature marshmallows.
Whip the cream cheese with sugar and mayonnaise.
When Jell-O is just set, mix all of these ingredients together with Cool Whip or whipping cream.
Freeze in a mold or oblong pan.

title: popovers
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and stir gradually into flour to make a smooth batter.
Beat thoroughly with eggbeater.
Fill greased custard cups or heavy muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 12 popovers.

title: asparagus gravy
directions: Wash, drain, and cut asparagus on bias.
Simmer asparagus in small amount of water until fork tender and then saute in bacon drippings.
Proceed with directions for cream gravy.
As far as I know this family favorite was created in Paris, Texas by someones Great-Uncle Billy over 70 years ago.
Serve for breakfast on biscuits.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, adding zucchini last.
Transfer to prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into 2-inch squares.

title: pennies from heaven
directions: Mix all ingredients well; add carrots last.
Refrigerate in covered dish overnight.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks.

title: zucchini and ham scallop
directions: Pare zucchini, dice and cook 7 minutes.
Drain thoroughly (1 1/2 cups).
Fork beat egg, combine egg, soup and milk.
Add diced ham, onion, drained zucchini and 3/4 cup Pepperidge Farm stuff mix; toss lightly.
Turn into oiled 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Combine the remaining 1/4 cup stuffing mix, oil and cheese; sprinkle over top of dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° about 1 hour.

title: elegant chicken(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Soak chicken in eggs for 1 hour.
Roll in Italian bread crumbs.
Saute in 1/2 cup butter until brown.

Layer in casserole with chicken broth, wine and pan drippings, mushrooms and grated cheese (I usually have 2 to 3 layers, ending with cheese on top). Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese begins to bubble and brown.

title: philly guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with juice.
Combine with all the rest of the ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in tomato.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: broccoli timbale
directions: Oil a 6-cup souffle mold and roll bread crumbs around interior, coating the bottom and sides.
Tap out the excess.
Cook the onions slowly in butter for about 10 minutes in a covered saucepan.
Do not allow them to color.
Put the onions, cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings into a mixing bowl and then beat in the eggs.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and oleo.
Add milk, egg, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake until golden brown at 350°, about 45 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine
meat,	rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup tomato soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 20 small balls and
place	in
skillet.
Mix remaining soup, water and Worcestershire
sauce;
pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil; reduce
heat, cover and simmer for 40 minutes, stirring often. Serves 4 or 5.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in casserole and add grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: seelbach cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars together with a paddle.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Mix all dry ingredients and incorporate into sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips and pecans; mix just long enough to incorporate evenly. Bake at 350° until outside layer is slightly firm and inside is soft.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: baptist pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with coconut or nuts. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: lory's cheesecake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Melt margarine on top of stove; saute onions and celery until soft.
Crumble baked cornbread and stale bread into large bowl. Pour butter and vegetables on bread; add broth and seasonings. Mix well.
Add water if you like it moister.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: uncooked play dough
directions: Mix the flour and salt in a large bowl or dishpan.
Pour the oil, water and food coloring into the flour mixture.
Mix until it has a consistency of bread dough. If dough is sticky, knead in a little more flour.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Put back in the same frypan and saute with one onion, salt and pepper.
Add the other ingredients and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and roll in nuts.
Chill.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk, egg yolks and lime juice.
Beat 1 egg white stiff.
Fold into milk mixture.
Beat 3 egg whites and gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Put into baked pie shell; bake until egg whites are golden brown at 350°.

title: rain's appetizers
directions: Mix cheese, olives, onions and mayonnaise.
Spread on bread slices.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Great for the holidays.

title: yum-yum egnops pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cream butter; stir in sugar, flour and egg yolks. Add lemon rind, lemon juice and milk. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Pour into pie shell. Bake for 12 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes more. Remove from oven; cool on rack. Serves 6.

title: raw cauliflower salad
directions: Mix a day or two before serving as it will be seasoned better. Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter with granulated and brown sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt and blend into the creamed mixture to make a smooth dough.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place in ungreased miniature tins.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Have miniature peanut butter cups ready, papers removed. Immediately after removing tray from oven, press a peanut butter cup into center of hot cookie.
Let cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes before removing cookies to tray.

title: bean salad
directions: Stir a few times and let all vegetables go through dressing.

title: new river chili
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and set aside.
Cook beef and onion; crumble and drain.
Combine macaroni, beef and remaining ingredients.
Stir and cover.
Simmer on low for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Makes 2 quarts.
Garnish with cheese.

title: "fresh corn" cornbread
directions: For when corn has begun to get too hard for boiling.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with taco chips.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water, add juices from oranges and pineapple.
Stir in fruit and cover with marshmallows. Let this congeal.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together. Spread over marshmallows.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Blend cake mix, butter and 3 eggs with fork.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (grease bottom only).
With mixer, beat 2 eggs, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over first mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Use 1/2 cup of mix with hot water.

title: cold oven chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and baking powder. Add cocoa, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and well-floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn heat to 350°. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese-swirled carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mushroom tarts
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle with water while mixing with a fork.
Form into a ball.
Divide dough into 24 balls.
Press each onto bottom and sides of miniature greased muffin pans.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon over dough.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: cucumber salad with spicy dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a medium salad bowl. Cover and chill.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, sugar, melted butter, salt, milk and water (measured in milk can) and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell; sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake at 350° until set and brown about 1 1/2 hours.

title: heavy cream sauce
directions: Combine ricotta cheese, cream cheese, juice and confectioners' sugar in food processor or in blender.
Process until smooth.
Add heavy cream and process just until blended. Great served with bread pudding or fruit crepes.

title: alice's chocolate frosting(never fail)
directions: Mix together and boil for 1 minute.
Beat until ready to spread.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Saute the onion in the oleo.
Mix all together except the cheese. Add the cheese.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cake(from 1925 watkins cookbook)
directions: Boil the first four ingredients and cool.
Mix together with remaining ingredients and add 2 cups flour.
Bake in moderate oven in layers.
Ice with chocolate icing and nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, onion and cooked broccoli.
Spread in 9 x 13 pan. Spread cheese on top of mixture.
Melt butter.
Mix together butter and stuffing.
Spread on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables according to package directions. Drain. Combine cooked vegetables, cheese, water chestnuts, onions and mayonnaise, stirring gently. Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: apple twists
directions: Cut each apple into eight pieces. Unroll crescent roll dough; separate into 8 triangles. Cut each in half lengthwise to make 16 triangle strips. Place an apple piece at wide end of each strip; roll up. Arrange in 9-inch square pan. Drizzle with margarine. Sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon & sugar. Drizzle with orange juice or water. Bake at 400° for 30-35 min. or until apples are tender. Serve warm, plain or with ice cream.

title: green bean puff
directions: Combine hot beans and celery in 5-cup casserole.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard, salt, vinegar and milk.
Fold in egg white. Pile lightly on bean mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until puffed and beans are heated.

title: curried split pea soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat just until boiling. Simmer 50 minutes or until peas are tender.
Puree in the blender.

title: pancakes
directions: Blend all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Beat in egg, shortening and milk.
Bake on a hot griddle.
Leftover batter can also be frozen.

title: chocolate icebox dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together flour and butter.
Add chopped nuts.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Remove from oven and cool crust.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 or 2 teaspoons of milk.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture over crust.
Mix the chocolate pudding and milk; mix until thick.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
May garnish with grated chocolate.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, sugar and oil until smooth.
Stir in sour cream making sure not to overmix.
Pour into a greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake in a 325° preheated oven for 1 hour.
If top gets to brown cover with aluminum foil.
Let cake cool before removing from pan.
Yields 10 - 12 slices.

title: microwave butterscotch pie
directions: In glass mixing bowl, put sugar, water and butter; microwave on High for 30 seconds, just until it starts to bubble.
Stir. Make paste of flour, cornstarch and a little milk.
Combine with sugar mixture using wire whisk; add rest of milk and egg yolks and mix well.
Microwave on High 4 minutes; whisk well and return to microwave for another 3 minutes.
If not thick enough, cook another minute.
Cover with plastic wrap and cool for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir again, then pour into pie shell.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: barbecue
directions: In frying pan, heat olive oil and add ground beef.
When partially cooked, add onion.
Stir and cook over medium heat. When meat is cooked, add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water and the sugar.
Boil 2 cups water and the tea bags.
Cool both mixtures.
Add booze, orange juice and lemonade; mix until frozen juice is melted.
Mix well and freeze.

title: shanghai beef
directions: Saute beef in large skillet until browned, about 5 minutes. Add cornstarch; blend well.
Add broth and veggies.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corine's carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix with first 3 ingredients.
Add grated raw carrots, nuts, raisins, orange rind and extract.
Bake in Pam-sprayed angel food cake pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked fish parmesan
directions: Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt in oven.
Set oven to 400°.
Place fish in dish and bake 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven; turn and baste.
Mix lemon juice and wine and pour over fish.
Sprinkle with seasonings and Parmesan cheese. Return to oven 10 more minutes.
Serve with rice and sauce from dish.

title: banana split dessert(bake off winner)
directions: Combine together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked spinach salad
directions: In casserole dish mix all ingredients in order given on top with bread crumbs and oil.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Spinach bakes in its own juice.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Cream shortening well.
Add sugar and blend together.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill.
Roll out 1/16-inch thick on pastry cloth.
Cut in designs.
Brush with egg white and decorate.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and blend thoroughly.
(It is important that the ingredients be evenly distributed.)
Divide on three 6-inch squares of aluminum foil.
Fold foil to make airtight packages.
Label.
Store in cool dry place.
Keeps up to 6 months.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until tests done.
Don't overbake. Frost with creme cheese icing.
Keeps well.
Can ice while hot.

title: salsa
directions: Mix and chill overnight, stirring occasionally.
You may coarsely chop in food processor, if you prefer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage, drain well.
Mix over low heat the cream cheese and sausage until well mixed.
Stuff mushroom caps with sausage and cheese mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pork chop with rice
directions: Brown pork chops in fat in pressure saucepan. Remove chops from pan. Add tomatoes, chopped onion, salt, pepper and rice. Lay pork chops over the top. Cover and bring to 15 pounds pressure. Cook 15 minutes.

title: strawberry-grapefruit cooler
directions: Combine first three ingredients in container of an electric blender. Cover and process until smooth.
With blender running, add ice cubes one at a time.
Process until smooth.
Serve immediately. Makes 3 cups.

title: sweet and sour brussels sprouts
directions: Cook sprouts in boiling salted water to cover for 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Meanwhile, saute bacon until crisp in a large skillet.
Remove bacon; drain on paper toweling, then crumble.

title: chicken divan
directions: In pan, layer partially cooked broccoli.
Cover broccoli with chicken meat.
Mix cream of celery soup, onion soup mix and mayonnaise.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and soup mixture is bubbly, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.
(May use turkey instead of chicken.)

title: jewish coffee cake(heritage recipe)
directions: Beat cake mix, pudding, oil, water, and eggs for 10 minutes. Grease and flour a 9 x 13 cake pan.
Pour 1/2 of batter into the pan.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray roaster with Pam.
Braise roast on medium-high heat on all sides in nonstick pan on top of stove (sprayed with Pam) until brown.
Place roast in roaster.
Reduce heat to medium.
Put about 1/2 pound onions in pan.
Saut until just brown.
Add marjoram and broth; bring to boil.
Pour into roaster over roast.
Cover roaster and cook approximately 2 hours. Then add remaining onions, potatoes and carrots.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Recover and cook approximately 1 hour or until vegetables done as desired.
In a small bowl, whisk together flour and water. Skim off visible fat from roast; put in pan with flour mixture, whisking until smooth.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cook 2 minutes or so.
Pour over roast and veggies.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in casserole dish in the order given. Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Bake at 325°
for 2 hours.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Cook noodles while browning hamburger.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 of sauce, 1/2 of cottage cheese and 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Melt margarine. Beat eggs, milk and sugar.
Mix with butter and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add nuts, coconut and graham cracker crumbs. Spread over graham crackers.
Top with crackers.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: chocolate mints
directions: In a large heavy saucepan over low heat, cook butter or margarine, sugar and water until butter is melted.
Add chocolate pieces and stir until partially melted.
Remove from heat and continue to stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Pour into large mixer bowl and let stand about 10 minutes to cool slightly. With mixer at high speed, beat in eggs one at a time.
Reduce speed to low and add dry ingredients, beating just until blended. Chill dough about 1 hour for easier handling.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Roll teaspoonfuls of dough into balls; place about 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 13 minutes, no longer.
Cookies will crisp as they cool. Remove from oven and immediately place mint on each hot cookie. Allow to soften, then swirl mint over cookie.
If desired, decorate with sprinkles.
Remove from cookie sheets and cool completely.
Makes 80 at about 90 calories each.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Then add all ingredients into mixing bowl (mix sugar and flour together before adding).
Pour into two ungreased 8-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (makes its own crust).
Cool completely before serving.

title: corn dogs
directions: Boil wieners as you would for hot dogs. Wipe dry, insert stick in wieners if you have them. If not serve on plate and eat with fork. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cornmeal, butter, milk and egg together. Coat wieners with batter; fry in deep fat until golden brown. Drain on paper towel. Serve while hot.

title: manicotti with cheese(serves 6)
directions: Cover manicotti shells with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain; rinse in cold water.
Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and 4 tablespoons Parmesan cheese; add parsley flakes, egg, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Place marinara sauce and water in medium saucepan.
Heat on low while stuffing manicotti. Preheat oven to 375°.
Stuff each manicotti shell with 1/3 to 1/2 cup cheese filling.
Pour 3/4 cup marinara sauce into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place stuffed noodles on top of sauce. Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: In medium bowl, place cauliflower, olives, green pepper, pimento and onion; set aside.
In jar with tight fitting lid, combine remaining ingredients.
Shake well.
Pour over cauliflower mixture.
In refrigerator, marinate, turning occasionally, for at least 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix thoroughly first 4 ingredients.
Blend and stir in flour and salt.
Roll dough into balls (1 teaspoon each).
Beat egg white slightly with fork. Dip balls in egg white.
Roll in nuts. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press thumb gently in center of each.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool and fill.

title: crunchy, munchy chicken
directions: Warm soup and 1/2 can milk on stove.
Arrange stuffing mix in large plate.
Dip chicken in warm soup, then roll both sides in stuffing mix.
Place chicken, skin side up, on broiler pan or other drip type pan.
Put dab (1/2 tablespoon) butter on each piece.
Place in oven at 375° to 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Just before serving, pour remaining soup over chicken.
Serve with white rice and a salad.

title: baked eggplant delight
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in pieces.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain and place in 1-1/2 to 2 quart casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 of cheese to spread on top.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Mix hamburger, taco seasoning and beans together; set aside.

title: black-eyed susans
directions: Cut 64 flower shapes from bread.
Whip cream cheese; add pineapple, chopped pecans and a little pineapple juice.
Spread filling on bread.
Put top on and garnish with olive slice.
Makes 32 small sandwiches.

title: baked onion rings
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first five ingredients and set aside.
Cut onions into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Separate into rings.
Beat egg substitute until frothy.
Dip onion rings into egg, then into crumb mixture, coating well.
Place in single layer on baking sheets that have been coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until onions are tender and coating is crispy.
Yield:
about 6 servings.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix above ingredients well and shape into balls. Bake in 300° oven about 45 minutes or until brown as you like. May be prepared ahead and frozen until needed. Store in freezer in baggie.

title: cleo's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Over the top, spread mixture of chicken or celery soup, shredded cheese and nuts.
On top of this, sprinkle crushed potato chips.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° to 375° oven.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt sugar and syrup together.
Mix peanut butter in.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Melt chips and pour over top.

title: peanut butter raisin bars
directions: In large saucepan, over medium heat, stir together brown sugar and corn syrup until sugar dissolves and mixture is warm.
Remove form heat, and blend in peanut butter.
Stir in cereal and raisins until well coated.
Press into lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cool until firm; cut into 24 bars.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 24 bars; 63 calories; 1 gram fat; 16 mg. sodium per bar.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/3 to 1/2 of mix into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon-cream tea loaf
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter, creaming well.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Combine lemon rind, lemon juice and powdered sugar, mixing until smooth; pour over hot loaves.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: curried shrimp in chutney
directions: Use the crab boil according to directions.
Boil 10 minutes. Add shrimp.
Boil 1 minute; clean if necessary.
Add curry powder to the chutney and either chop into very small pieces or put into blender.
Melt butter.
Pour in butter.
Mix well.
Serve hot in a chafing dish.
(Good over rice or as hors d'oeuvres for cocktail buffet.)

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Stir together flour, pudding and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and butter with dry ingredients.
Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Lightly beat together eggs, mustard and seasoned salt.
Dip chicken in mustard mixture, then roll in potato flakes until well coated.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Arrange chicken, skin side down, in pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer until tender and brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream 2 minutes the shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs, salt and vanilla.
Then mix in flour, soda, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Mix and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.
Makes a large batch. Delicious every time.

title: basic graham cracker crust
directions: Crush the graham crackers by placing squares on a piece of wax paper and rolling over them with a rolling pin.
Place all the ingredients together and mix with a fork until moistened.
Press into pie pan that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Yields one 8 or 9-inch crust (8 servings).

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli, then layer broccoli, chicken, dots of butter and garlic salt in greased casserole dish. Mix soup, sour cream, milk, 1 cup grated cheese and sherry. Heat. Pour over meat and broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese, paprika and almonds. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: victoria fudge
directions: Combine cream, butter and sugar.
Boil to soft ball stage. Remove from fire.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat until creamy. Add chopped fruit and coconut.
Add flavoring.
Pour into well buttered, shallow pan.
Cut in squares.

title: brunch souffle
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Crumble sausage into bowl. Beat eggs in another bowl.
Add milk, salt, mustard and bread cubes; mix well.
Add cheese and sausage; mix again.
Spoon into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate overnight. Remove dish from refrigerator.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until egg mixture is set.
Cut into squares to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in a double boiler until thick, then put into a cooked pie crust.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix 3 ingredients by hand, folding together.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freezes well.

title: orange fluff cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter or shortening together.
Put egg whites
into
a
separate bowl.
Add yolks to the creamed mixture. Add
orange
juice
and rind.
Blend dry ingredients and
liquids alternately.
Fold
lightly beaten egg whites in last.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: saffron and shrimp paella
directions: In a paella pan, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add shrimp; saute until pink, about 2 minutes.
Transfer shrimp to a bowl. Add onion, garlic and fennel to pan; saute over low heat until slightly soft, about 7 minutes.
Add zucchini and tomatoes; saute 3 minutes longer.
Add rice; stir.
Add saffron with liquid, salt, pepper and hot water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and cook until rice is done, about 20 minutes.
Return shrimp to pan.
Stir in chopped zucchini; turn off heat.
Cover and let sit 10 minutes. Fluff and serve topped with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, saute garlic and green pepper until tender; remove and set aside.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Cook 30 minutes or until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce and green pepper; simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Place pasta in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spoon chicken and sauce over pasta. Bake, covered, for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: cheese stuffed cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower into boiling salted water until tender but still firm.
Drain.
Place whole head in shallow baking pan. Press sticks into cauliflower all over head.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix olive oil and bread crumbs and press mixture onto cauliflower.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are lightly brown.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place tomatoes in a colander in sink in 1 layer. Sprinkle with salt and allow to drain for 10 minutes. Layer tomato slices, basil and onion in pie shell. Season with salt and pepper. Combine the grated cheeses and mayonnaise. Spread mixture on top of tomatoes. Bake for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Add eggs, Parmesan cheese and butter to hot noodles and form into a 10-inch pie dish like a crust.
Put cottage cheese in center of crust.

title: mexican fiesta cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together one bowl, blending well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar. Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together. Add eggs, milk, flavoring and dry mixture alternately, beating thoroughly. Bake in greased tube pan at 350° until done, about 90 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in an 11 x 15-inch pan.
Mix with crumbs.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crust.
Cover with chocolate chips. Sprinkle with coconut.
Spread nuts over top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: baked eggplant parmigiano
directions: Wash eggplant and peel skin off.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Combine egg and water and beat in a shallow bowl.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture, then into bread crumbs.
Saute in olive oil until brown and tender.
In a casserole dish, place eggplant slices in layers, alternating with sauce, seasonings and cheese. Bake in covered casserole dish at 375° fo 30 to 40 minutes.
Can serve with pasta.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in two 8-inch pans or 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool cake and frost.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and mold in a loaf pan; turn out in a shallow baking dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Blend sugar and margarine into pretzels.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't overbake. Let cool

title: wonderful cole slaw
directions: *Open Ramen packages and set aside seasoning packets. (See **.)

title: b's lasagna
directions: Brown beef with salt.
Add basil, tomato sauce and paste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Boil noodles, shred cheese.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs, add cottage cheese, Parmesan, salt and pepper.
Smear 9 x 13 pan with meat mix.
Layer noodles, egg mixture.
Sprinkle with mozzarella.
Repeat, ending with mozzarella on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or refrigerate and bake the next day for 45 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans. In a mixing bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add shortening and bananas; beat on low speed of electric mixer until combined.
Add buttermilk or sour milk, eggs and vanilla; beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Turn batter into prepared pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes on wire racks.
Remove from pans; cool thoroughly.
Frost with creamy butter frosting.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Stir together milk and lemon juice. Mix in pie filling and Cool Whip. Pour into 9 x 9 inch pan and freeze overnight.

title: maple and brown sugar meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: candy bar brownies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir into sugar mixture.
Fold in chopped nougat bars.
Spoon into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; sprinkle with chopped milk chocolate bars.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat
eggs,
add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Then add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 325° in loaf pans 1 hour, or 40 muffins for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes about 3 loaves.
Test with toothpicks.

title: carrot cake frosting
directions: Bring milk and flour to a boil; this will be very thick.
Cool. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add cooled mixture and mix at high speed with mixer; add vanilla.
Frosting will be light and fluffy.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk in a large bowl.
Whisk until thickened. Add Cool Whip, mix well.
Add bananas and vanilla wafers; stir together.
Smooth top with spoon.
Crumble a few wafers over top -- then enjoy.

title: apple fritters
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift dry ingredients together.
Add apple.
Stir in milk and eggs.
Put skillet over high heat and add oil to a depth of 1-inch.
Drop batter by teaspoon into hot oil and fry until golden brown (about 2 to 3 minutes).
Remove and drain. Repeat cooking step until all batter is used.
Serve with syrup.

title: graham cracker toffee bars
directions: Mix and bring to boil. Butter and line a cookie sheet with graham crackers. Pour mixture over crackers. Sprinkle 1 c. pecans over top. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. When edges turn dark brown, its done.

title: wrapped cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent rolls and press seams together.
Place cheese in the middle and wrap bread around it. Seal and brush with beaten egg.
Bake until golden brown.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter together.
Add eggs; beat together.
Add 1/2 cup of milk and flour with baking powder and salt.
Stir in lemon rind and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Take out of pan and pour juice of lemon, mixed with 1/2 cup sugar, over the bread.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook seasoned rice, using directions on package.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Chop chicken and mix all together.
Add 1 cup chicken broth.
Put in buttered casserole dish and bake 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.
Makes 5 cups.

title: strawberry cup
directions: Put herbs in a pot and pour in the wine.
Cover and let stand in a cool place for 3 hours.
Lightly sweeten strawberries with honey.
Put them in the wine and herb liquid and add sparkling water before serving.
Make sure everyone gets a strawberry in each glass.
Yield: Serves 16.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Roll thin and cut in strips.
Add to boiling chicken broth.
Boil chicken until tender (boney parts and gizzard; do not add liver) about 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 6 cups of water.
Chicken tastes better if soaked in salt water overnight.

title: currant-studded bulgur
directions: Combine water, currants, honey, salt, black pepper, cinnamon and cumin in a medium-size saucepan.
Bring to simmering.
Stir in bulgur and green onions.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 10 minutes or until the bulgur is tender.
(Can be made up to a day ahead and refrigerated.)

title: creamy pinwheels
directions: On a piece of wax paper, use a rolling pin or a sturdy plastic glass to flatten the slices of raisin bread.
(Plain bread may also be used.)

title: pecan balls
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream margarine, sugar and flour.
Add pecans and mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 45 minutes.
Stir together confectioners sugar and granulated sugar in small bowl.
Roll baked cookies in sugar mixture while still hot.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Add cabbage to margarine.
Steam cabbage about 10 minutes (no water)
Add lemon for odor.
Add salt, pepper, celery seed and corned beef.
Chill before slicing for easier slicing.
Can put cooked carrots on top.

title: orange smoothee
directions: Measure grape juice and water to equal a gallon.
Add 1 1/2 to 4 pounds of sugar.
Grapes half and half.
I use juice straight, it takes longer in cool weather.
Oak casket, add water as needed for it to boil out sediments.
(The more sugar, the more potent.) Leave until it stops bubbling over.

title: miracle salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Sprinkle Jell-O over mixture and stir until distributed.
Set in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: Saute
chopped onions and green peppers in butter, in a large saucepan.
Add ham chunks, potato, water, bouillon cube and corn. Simmer
until
potato
is tender, about 15 minutes. Add milk
and crushed
crackers;	stir
until it returns to a simmer.
Serves 6.

title: salmon and fresh dill cheesecake
directions: Position oven rack 7-inches from broiler element.
Preheat broiler.
Line a jelly roll pan or small baking pan with aluminum foil.
Place salmon on prepared pan.
Season with seasoned salt and white pepper.
Place 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine, cut into pieces, on top.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix together
oil,
sugar
and	eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and
cinnamon.
Add
vanilla, apples and nuts.
Mix well. Grease and flour
angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Let cool
for 30 minutes and take out of pan.
(Do not tip pan upside down to cool.)

title: shrimp south louisiana
directions: Wash and peel raw shrimp; set aside.
Make a roux by heating shortening in a deep skillet.
Add flour and cook on medium heat until dark brown, stirring constantly.
Add chopped onions, pepper, celery and garlic.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies and tomato sauce.
Season with salt and pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Let simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Bring to boiling point.
Add shrimp and cook 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: frito salad
directions: Mix tomatoes, peppers, onion, beans, cheese, and dressing. Chill.
Stir in Fritos just before serving.

title: lemon rice soup
directions: Cover stewer in heavy soup pot with water.
Add carrot, onion, celery,
salt and peppercorns;
simmer until chicken is tender. Strain broth.
Add rice or rosamarina;
cook 20 to 25 minutes. Remove
from
heat.
Beat
egg
whites
until frothy (stiff but not dry).
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and slowly add lemon juice.
Add
broth, a little at a time (about 2 cups of broth). Then
pour mixture into pot; stir well.
Chunks of chicken may be added.
Serve immediately.

title: sausage cheese muffins
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until no longer pink; drain.
In a bowl, combine soup, milk, sage and sausage. Stir in the biscuit mix just until moistened.
Fill regular greased muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until muffins test done.
Yield: 2 dozen muffins.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage (uncooked) and cheese with your hands. Set at room temperature for 30 minutes. Add Bisquick in 3 to 4 parts; mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until browned. Makes 40 to 50 balls.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Place graham crackers in single layer in 9 x 9-inch glass pan to cover bottom of pan.
Cover with layer of pudding (1 cup).
Repeat layers of crackers and pudding, ending with pudding.
Crumble a few crackers to sprinkle around edges of cake.

title: fat-free mexican casserole
directions: Layer bottom of casserole dish with flour tortillas (it is easier to use them whole and not tear into pieces).
Mix 1/2 of taco seasoning mix with refried beans and spread 1/2 of beans for next layer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix instant potatoes for 6; reduce liquid (1 3/4 cups water). Add cream cheese, sour cream and garlic salt.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle on chives and paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream puffs(good)
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil; then add flour and salt. Mix until forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet by tablespoonfuls. Bake in 400° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked whole shad
directions: Grease fish inside and out with cooking oil.
Stuff with stuffing mix, celery and onion (very wet).
Fold aluminum foil tightly over fish and lay it in a baking pan.
Put a small amount of water in the baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 6 hours.
(The bones will melt away.)

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Whip the cream.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.
Chill.

title: broccoli and cashews
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; do not overcook.
Place drained broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and set aside.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream, sugar, vinegar, poppy seed, salt and paprika. Pour over top of broccoli.
Sprinkle with cashew nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until heated through.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bubble bread
directions: Pour over rolls in order listed in Bundt pan and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool in pan at least 15 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: cold green beans
directions: Let green beans, onion, salad oil, vinegar, salt and pepper stand 1 hour or overnight.
Drain.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, mustard and horseradish.

title: mediterranean green beans
directions: Saute onion and celery in olive oil until onion is transparent (do not brown).
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lucy kammerdiener's mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine and sift flour, baking soda, sugar, cocoa and salt. Add mayonnaise, cold water and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour batter into two greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes.

title: peaches for tarts or fried pies
directions: Wash, core, peel and cut pears or apples in pieces.
To prevent darkening, drop into water containing 2 teaspoons salt and vinegar per gallon of water.
Drain, then boil 5 minutes in syrup. Pack fruit into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover with hot syrup.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath (pints 15 minutes and quarts 20 minutes).

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot on medium heat.
After heated through, simmer for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine
potatoes,
butter, egg yolks, brown sugar, salt and spices.
Stir
in milk, mix well.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) on high
speed
with
electric mixer for 1 minute. Gradually add the 1/4
cup	sugar,	1
tablespoon
at
a
time, beating until stiff
and
peaks
form.
Fold
egg
whites
into potato mixture.
Spoon into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce
heat to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until set.
Yield: 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Combine all ingredients, then fill shells.
Spread a thin layer of spaghetti sauce on bottom of a 13x9 pan.
Put in shells and poor sauce over.
Cover with foil and bake 350 degrees for about 30-35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Add ingredients in order.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Frost or dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: potatoes and pork chop casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and bake until done.

title: kassie's chili
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion together.
Drain fat.
Mix all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cover.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add sour cream and milk.
Season to taste.
Cover bottom of shallow pan with croutons and pour mushroom mixture over.
Top with diced cheese.
Do not stir.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Delicious. Serves 8 to 10.
Great main dish.

title: broccoli and mushroom quiche
directions: In
medium
bowl
beat	eggs with whisk.
Add cream and beat. Add
salt.	Pour
broccoli	and
mushrooms in bottom of crust; sprinkle
with
cheese.
Pour
cream
and egg mix over this.
Dot with butter. Put pan on cookie sheet and carefully slip
into 350°
oven.
Cook
minutes or until quiche has puffed
up into a dome and slightly browned.
Allow to cool at least 1/2 hour. Serves 8.

title: veggie blend
directions: Steam vegetables 10 minutes; drain off water.
Place vegetables in casserole dish and add cheese and mayonnaise to vegetables.
Mix thoroughly.
Top with crushed crackers and chips. Melt butter and pour over vegetable casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated throughout casserole.

title: dill dip(vegetables)
directions: Mix together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator and stir before serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale. When ready to serve, add ginger ale and stir well.

title: lenten soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in oil for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until soft.
Add approximately 4 to 5 cups of water depending on how thick you prefer the soup.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken siu mai
directions: Mix fish cake and chicken.
Add in finely diced water chestnuts, mushrooms and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix filling well.
Using a spoon or butter knife, put filling on wrapper.
Squeeze up the sides, shaping siu mai in hand.
Put upright in steamer and steam 30 minutes, until cooked well.
Enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done-cut into pieces and place in casserole pan.

title: swedish three layer bars
directions: Use a beater and mix together; spread on top of other layers. Let cool about 1 hour and then cut into bars.
I personally freeze or refrigerate for several hours before trying to cut.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Make sure all ingredients are dry.
In a large bowl, start with lettuce, then red peppers, green onions, celery, fried bacon and sweet peas.
Spread mayonnaise on top of peas.
Sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise.
Layer with cheese, then top with bacon. Top with olives, if desired.
Chill for 4 to 5 hours.

title: chocolate peanut cluster
directions: Melt milk chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, peanut butter and paraffin in a double boiler over boiling water.
Add roasted peanuts.
Dip onto waxed paper.
Makes approximately 80 clusters.

title: cheese-puffed potato casserole
directions: Beat egg yolks with mashed potatoes until well blended.
Stir in cheese and seasonings.
Before baking, beat egg whites until stiff and fold into potato mixture.
Spoon into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes.
Serves about 6.

title: crock-pot camp stew
directions: Chop onion and saute in crock-pot on high setting.
Chop potatoes and mash tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients and cook on high until starts to boil, then turn to low and cook several hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: Butter bread, cube and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese, sausage, red pepper and onions over bread. In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, soup, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread mixture; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: white bread
directions: In large pan, combine 8 cups flour, 2 tablespoons yeast, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon salt and 9 tablespoons dry milk.
Mix with spoon, then make a well and add salad oil and water.
Beat by hand for about 5 minutes until it looks smooth and shiny.
Then add a couple of cups of flour and beat again.
Keep adding flour until you can work it with your hands.
Then sprinkle a little flour under the dough and keep kneading until the dough doesn't stick to your hands.
(You may need more flour than 10 cups.)
Turn over and grease top and cover.
Set on a pan of hot water to rise for 2 hours, then work down and divide into three 3 x 12-inch loaf pans. Set on warm water and let rise 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: For color, add small amounts of chopped pimento and/or green peppers.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients except poppy seed in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Add poppy seed and stir.
Grease 2 bread tins. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: paula's swedish nut cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add eggs, juice and oil. Mix at high speed for 1 minute, then medium until well blended. Add walnuts and vanilla; mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Poke with a toothpick until it comes out clean.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Place hominy in baking dish.
Combine soup, cream, celery seed, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and cayenne pepper in saucepan; simmer until flavors are well mixed. Stir in almonds.
Pour over hominy.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken coleslaw
directions: Mix chicken and cabbage in a bowl.
Add basil, onion and cilantro.
Mix vinegar, hot pepper, salt and sugar to make dressing.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture, right before serving.
Sprinkle peanuts on top.

title: rice galare
directions: Mix jello, sugar and pineapple.
Cook rice with water until tender.
While hot, mix with the jello mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Put in refrigerator until set.
Whip the whipping cream until thick and add to set jello mixture.
Add miniature marshmallows (optional).

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix together soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots and let set for at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Mix ingredients together over hot water.
Spread half of mixture on a jelly roll pan, 17 x 11 1/2-inch.
Chill until firm. Melt butter.
Add milk and pudding mix.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add maple flavoring.
Add sugar and blend until smooth.
Spread this mixture on cooled first layer.
Cool.
Mix peanuts into remaining half of chocolate mixture and spread on top of cooled second layer.
Chill; cut into small squares as this bar is very rich.

title: swiss style sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until limp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover. Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans until fluffy. Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours. Shape into a ball. Roll in pecans; cover. Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: triple chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs and milk; beat well. Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture, blending well.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: broccoli-mushroom spaghetti
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Stir in drained mushrooms, margarine, salt and pepper.
Heat over low heat.
Stir occasionally until mushrooms are hot, about 5 minutes.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Toss spaghetti and broccoli mixture with Parmesan cheese and lemon juice.
Serve with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: copper pennies
directions: Layer ingredients in a deep casserole.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar, mixing well.
Heat butter, Coca-Cola and cocoa.
Bring to a boiling point.
Pour over flour and sugar. Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla; mix well.
Add marshmallows and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
The marshmallows will rise to the top during baking.
For the best results, evenly distribute the marshmallows in the pan before baking.

title: nahiku nut pine pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend 1/3 cup of sugar, cornstarch and pineapple.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and clear. Cool.
Blend cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar, salt and eggs, added one at a time.
Stir well.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Spread pineapple mixture when cooled into pie shell.
Pour in cream cheese mixture and sprinkle with Macadamia nuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce oven to 325° and bake an additional 50 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add egg and milk.
Beat with mixer until smooth. Dip 1 pound of wieners in batter and fry in hot, deep fryer until both sides are brown.
Drain on paper towels; serve hot.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix chicken with wine and half of cornstarch.
Drain pineapple and pickles, reserving juice.
Heat oil in a large frying pan to medium-low temperature.
Add garlic and heat until it begins to brown.
Remove garlic.
Add chicken to oil in pan and stir-fry about 3 minutes until opaque.
Remove from heat.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Add dressing.
Cover and refrigerate.
Drain and serve.
These improve with age and are best made 4 to 5 days before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in loaf pan.

title: hamburger corn pie
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, sausage, onion and garlic until meat is brown; drain.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, corn, olives, chili powder and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Pour in ungreased baking dish (9 x 9 x 2-inch) or 2 quart casserole. Mix cornmeal, milk and eggs.
Pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Garnish with parsley sprigs and black olives if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage get to room temperature.
With hands, mix sausage, Bisquick and work in grated cheese.
Make into little balls (one heaping tablespoonful).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix.
Spoon into buttered muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute onions and peppers in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add hamburger meat.
Cook until red color leaves meat.
Add soup and tomato sauce.
Add macaroni. Mix.
Pour into baking dish. Top with mild Cheddar cheese and bake until cheese melts at 350° (about 10 minutes).

title: easy prune cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and cloves in large mixer bowl; mix well.
Add oil, eggs and prunes; beat well.
Stir in pecans. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cover with foil immediately.
May drizzle with favorite glaze, if desired.
This cake freezes well.
Cake will be moister if placed in freezer while still hot.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until resembles coarse meal.
Combine the egg and milk and add to flour mixture.
Stir until all these ingredients are moistened.
Turn onto floured surface and knead about 10 times.
Roll to 1-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter (about 2 1/2-inch size).
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden.
Yields about 15 biscuits.

title: russian salad
directions: Add lime Jell-O to 1 cup boiling water.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
May keep on low heat until dissolved.
Take off heat.
Cool.
Add pineapple, nuts and 1 cup cold water.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: creole corn
directions: Saute onions in margarine; stir in flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat until thickened or bake on slow heat until brown.

title: peanutty corn crunchies
directions: Boil sugar, honey and peanut butter 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir in cereal and raisins.
Press into 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Cut into 36 squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies, reserve 1/2 c for topping.
Mix remaining crumbs with melted margarine and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese, then fold in half of cool whip.
Spread over cookie crust.
Make pudding with 1 3/4 cups milk and pour over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining cool whip and sprinkle with reserved cookie crumbs, and refrigerate 1 more hour before serving.
Serves 24.

title: lifesaver cake
directions: Coat any kind cake with any kind icing (preferably cream cheese icing).
Stick Lifesavers all over cake.
This makes a colorful cake to brighten someone's day or at Christmastime.

title: lemon cheesecake(delicious low-fat dessert)
directions: Coat a 9-inch spring-form pan with cooking spray; dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Combine tofu with next 8 ingredients in container of blender or food processor; process until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time; process until just blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven; cool cheesecake in oven for 1 hour.
Cover and chill.
Remove sides of pan when ready to serve; top with sliced strawberries and lemon. Makes 12 servings.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Mix room temperature cream cheese and pineapple.
Add cherries.
Add a few drops of cherry juice to sweeten dip.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cool cake layers completely.
Prepare pudding mix and refrigerate.
Place 1 layer cake in bottom of punch bowl (6-quart size).
Add 1/2 of ingredients.
Add other cake layer and remaining ingredients.
Garnish with coconut, pecans and cherries. Serves 35.

title: cocktail barbecue wieners
directions: Mix on low heat.
Add 1 to 2 pounds of wieners (cut into bite sizes).
Use toothpicks for serving.

title: pumpkin bran muffins
directions: Combine bran cereal, pumpkin, milk, corn syrup and egg whites in one bowl and set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and baking powder together and add to first bowl of ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Add raisins.
Spread batter into 12 section muffin tin coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pink artic freeze
directions: Soften cheese. Blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into gelatin mold and freeze until firm.
