title: georgia bars
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil; cook 1 minute. Add nuts, coconut and cracker crumbs. Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Line with whole graham crackers. Pour filling over these and spread. Top with more graham crackers and spread on icing.

title: hamburg noodle bake
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Cook noodles; combine with ground beef and onion.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Cut cheese into small cubes; add to noodle mixture.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.

title: fat free nacho dip
directions: Layer on a serving plate and serve with salsa and fat free tortilla chips.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup fruit juice, let thicken but not all the way.
Stir in 2 cups of whipped topping and the pineapple.
Refrigerate to complete set.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: hot cranberry compote(microwave recipe!)
directions: In microwave dish put fruit and cranberry sauce with wooden spoon.
Stir until sauce is broken up.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and microwave for another minute or two.
Serve hot. Makes a good side dish for pork, beef or poultry.
Good way to use odds and ends of fruit and leftover cranberry sauce.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook the ground beef and taco seasoning according to package directions.
Simmer until "no juice" left.
Add the sour cream; simmer.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 2 cans of crescent rolls. Add a layer of crushed Doritos, 1/2 of the meat mixture and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat the layers, using Mozzarella cheese instead of Cheddar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sour cream, lettuce and tomatoes on the side.

title: french fried onions
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Sift dry ingredients together. Slowly add lemon juice.
Mix in water.
Then add oil.
Stir until smooth, fold in egg whites.
Dip onion rings in batter and fry until golden brown.

title: speedy tuna skillet
directions: Saute onions in butter until almost tender.
Add soup, milk and peas.
Cover and heat just to boiling, stirring occasionally. Add tuna and dash of pepper.
Heat through.
Serve over warm crisp chow mein noodles or hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Brown garlic in oil.
Let oil cool.
Add tomatoes, basil and oregano; simmer for 40 minutes.
Add wine; simmer an additional 5 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Serve over pasta or in lasagna dishes.

title: ting-a-ling(candy)
directions: Prepare cookie sheets with wax paper.
Melt chips over hot (not boiling) water.
When completely melted, stirring gently, add peanuts and noodles, gently tossing until thoroughly blended. Drop heaping teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Chill until hardened. Peel from wax paper; store in box or can.
Keeps for months; ships perfectly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ingredients and form a loaf.
Place in shallow pan in moderate oven (350°).
While it is starting to bake, combine sauce ingredients.

title: sour cream coffeecake(serves 9)
directions: In small bowl, combine walnuts, cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar. Grease Bundt pan.
In large bowl at medium speed, beat butter with 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and remaining ingredients and beat at low speed until blended.
Increase speed to medium; beat 3 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1/2 of batter in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of nut mixture.
Spread evenly with remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining nut mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until cake pulls away from side of pan.
Cool cake in pan completely on wire rack.

title: kraut, noodle and mushroom dish
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions together in margarine.
Rinse sauerkraut and add to mushroom mixture.
Cook pasta and add to mixture.
Add pepper to taste and heat throughout.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put squash, salt and water together in pot and cook until done.
Drain.
Add margarine, sour cream, cheese and black pepper. Pour into 3-quart dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: waffles
directions: Mix egg yolks and milk.
Add dry ingredients and only mix. Don't beat until smooth.
Add oil, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cook in waffle iron.
Any leftover batter may be stored in the refrigerator.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt bark and peanut butter together over low heat, stirring to prevent burning. Mix other ingredients in large bowl. Pour melted bark over mixture. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Makes about 90 cookies. Freezes well.

title: chili mix
directions: Mix all and cook for 1 hour.
Pour in jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.
May be stored in freezer bags until ready for use.

title: mini fruitcake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs, honey and vanilla until fluffy.

title: chicken cacciatore(very good)
directions: Put sliced onion in bottom of crock-pot.
Add chicken pieces. Stir together tomato paste, mushrooms, salt, pepper, garlic, herbs, white wine and water.
Spread over chicken.
Cover; cook on low 7 to 9 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).
Serve chicken pieces over hot spaghetti or vermicelli.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream together butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix in pretzels and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 6 minutes.
Let cool.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix together and chill 1 hour.
Then roll in balls the size of hickory nuts. Place on baking sheet and press with a fork. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, put chicken and cream of chicken soup.
Add broth and vegetables; stir well. Pour into baking dish (with melted butter).
Stir together flour and milk; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 1 hour 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry
ingredients
into a 9 x 9-inch pan; mix well. Make 3
holes.
Pour
oil,
vinegar
and
vanilla in separate holes. Pour water over all; mix well with fork (do not beat). Bake at 350°
for
minutes.
Leave in pan and frost while still warm.

title: honorable chicken oriental
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Preheat grill.
Brush chicken pieces with oil.
Grill over low-medium heat 45 to 60 minutes, turning frequently.
Brush with sauce after first 20 minutes and continue until done.
Pass remaining sauce.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Combine
cake mix and peanut butter; beat with electric mixer on	medium	speed
until
coarse crumbs form.
Continue following package directions for cake mix, but omit oil.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems off mushrooms, chop and put in frying pan with butter.
Saute until light brown.
Put tops into a bowl, pour boiling water over them and steam for 5 minutes.
Pour water off and stuff with dressing.

title: fettuccine with smoked salmon and fresh peas(serves 4)
directions: Cook pasta in large kettle of lightly salted boiling water until al dente.
Drain and toss lightly with olive oil.
Set aside in warm place.
Blanch peas in pot of lightly salted water for 3 minutes.
Drain and plunge into ice water.
Drain again.
Set aside.
Put 4 slices smoked salmon, 2 tablespoons cream and shallots in blender; puree until smooth and creamy; set aside. Bring Dubonnet to boil in heavy saucepan.
Add remaining cream and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture coats back of spoon.
Add salmon puree and blend; stir over low heat until mixture is hot. Season with salt and pepper.
Cut remaining salmon into thin strips.
In large serving dish, toss the pasta with the peas and salmon.
Pour the hot sauce over it; toss well.
Serve immediately.

title: crusty white braids
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 2 cups of the unbleached flour and the yeast. Add sugar and salt to dry mixture. Whisk well. Add water and the canola oil. Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping the sides of the bowl constantly with the mixer. Beat 3 minutes at high speed. By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough. Turn out onto lightly floured surface; knead the dough until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Get your hands, elbows and shoulders into it. You will feel it change consistency after 5+ minutes. Keep kneading until it is quite pliable. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface; knead the dough until smooth and elastic, perhaps another 8 to 10 minutes. Take your time; knead before an open window so you can take on a Ferdinand the Bull outlook to the gentleness of all of life around you. Shape the dough into a ball. Place dough in a greased bowl, turning once to grease entire surface.

title: apple butter
directions: Core and slice apples, but do not peel.
Add only enough water to cook apples until soft.
Press through a fine sieve and measure 8 cups pulp.
Add vinegar, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook combined ingredients until mixture remains in a smooth mass when a little is cooled.
This will require about 1 1/2 hours gentle cooking. During cooking, stir frequently to prevent burning.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal while hot.
To eliminate the possibility of mold forming, process the jars 10 minutes in boiling water bath. Makes 5 pints.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a full boil, then remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour mixture over corn flakes; mix well.
Shape into round balls while still hot.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Combine ingredients, including broccoli.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until set, 15 or 20 minutes.
Crush potato chips or crackers and put on top.
Put in oven to brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, soda and salt in bowl.
Add sugar, egg, vanilla and butter.
Add nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pineapple over cherries. Sprinkle cake mix over cherries and pineapple. Pour melted margarine over top of cake mix. Sprinkle nuts and coconut over butter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: alaska sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil butter and water.
Mix sugar, flour and salt together; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together; add to the sugar mixture and beat.
Pour into a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: feather molasses cake
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients	 together.
Combine
molasses, shortening, eggs and vanilla
in
separate	bowl and mix well. Add to dry ingredients and
mix well.
Pour boiling water over all and mix.

title: ham and cheese pockets
directions: Thaw pastry about 20 minutes at room temperature.
Roll each sheet of pastry into a 12-inch square on a lightly floured board. Cut into nine 4-inch squares.
Repeat with remaining sheets of pastry.
Spread each square lightly with mustard.
Cut cheese and ham into 3 1/2 x 2-inch strips.
Top each half of square with a strip of cheese.
Place a strip of ham over each cheese strip. Fold squares of pastry into halves in line with the long edges of ham strips.
Moisten edges and pressing with a fork to seal.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in a large pot until tender. Remove chicken.
Cut in big chunks.
Cook spaghetti 5 minutes in chicken broth. Add cheese, butter and soup.
Layer with chicken or mix all together. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Put in large casserole dish or 2 medium size, buttered.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: pear marmalade
directions: Wash and remove peeling from oranges.
Add 1 quart water to peelings; boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and discard water.
Add another quart of water; boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and discard. Grind peel and oranges together.
Wash, remove core from pears and cut pears into small pieces.
Combine oranges, pears and pineapple; measure.
Add half as much sugar as fruit mixture.
Add lemon juice; mix thoroughly.
Cook rapidly until almost thick, about 40 minutes.
Add cherries; cook 5 minutes longer.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Saute onion.
Cut up squash; boil with 1 tablespoon sugar until soft.
Add onion to chicken soup.
Add chopped parsley and onions.
Drain and mash squash and add to soup mixture.
Put through blender briefly.
Add cream and melted butter.
Stir briefly.
Serve immediately.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix cheeses together.
Layer half of mixture in casserole dish.
Spread on half of sour cream.
Sprinkle on 1/4 cup almonds, 1/4 teaspoon cumin, and half of peppers.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or bread.

title: microwave corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in a 1 1/2 quart glass casserole for 30 seconds. Stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Cook covered for 9 minutes, stirring once.
Let stand, loosely covered, 2 minutes before serving.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Place in large container with 2 gallons of water and lime.
Soak 24 hours.
Then rinse well.
Soak 3 hours in clear cold water, changing water every hour.
Place cucumbers in pot and set aside.
If you don't like spice in your pickles, you may tie the spice in a cloth (one tablespoon per cloth).
Place vinegar, salt, sugar and spice in pot and bring to a boil.
Then pour over cucumbers and let set overnight.
Next morning, bring to boil and then cook 35 minutes.
Place hot pickles in 9 pint jars and seal.

title: asparagus-n-peas
directions: No salt is necessary.

title: jalapeno pepper casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Let cream cheese soften at room temperature and then spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Put chili and cooked ground beef on top of cheese.
Then put a layer of peppers.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: honey raisin nibbles
directions: Mix raisins, honey and peanut butter.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls into coconut, rolling until coated.
Place on waxed paper and refrigerate several hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix soup, mayo, lemon juice, curry and cheese.
Cook broccoli; place in greased casserole.
Cover with cooked cut-up chicken; cover with soup mixture.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake in a quart jar.

title: tomato-onion relish
directions: Saute garlic in oil until lightly browned (1 to 2 minutes). Stir in onions and pepper flakes.
Saute for 3 minutes. Stir in tomatoes.
Lower heat.
Cover and cook 5 minutes. Uncover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in vinegar and black pepper. Cool. Refrigerate unless using immediately. Stir in basil just before serving.

title: corn and green bean pudding
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, using sharp knife, cut corn kernels from cob.
Thinly slice green beans diagonally.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook green beans 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add corn; cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
In large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, flour, salt and pepper; stir in evaporated milk until blended.
Stir in corn mixture.
Preheat oven to 325°. Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour corn mixture into casserole. Place casserole in 13 x 9-inch baking pan or other small dish with about 1-inch water.
Bake until done, approximately 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife inserted halfway to the middle comes out clean.

title: no sugar jam
directions: Combine ingredients and wait 1 minute. Cook till thick. Store in refrigerator.

title: 15 minute fettucini alfredo
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, oleo and milk over low heat until smooth.
Add fettucini; toss lightly.

title: deviled lobster
directions: Chop lobster as fine as possible or put through a meat grinder.
Mix rest of ingredients with lobster so as to form a paste.
Serve with potato chips.

title: brown rim cookies
directions: Mix and spoon drop on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until rim of cookie is brown. (about 10 minutes)

title: nacho-hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. In medium saucepan, mix soup and enchilada sauce; bring to small boil over medium heat, stirring to avoid scorching. Add Velveeta cheese and stir until cheese melts; remove from heat.

title: dairy queen ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour in churn.
Mix until frozen. Makes 4 quarts.

title: no bake chocolate peanut cookies
directions: Wipe interior of 3-quart saucepan with butter just below rim. Combine milk, sugar, cocoa, peanut butter and butter in pan.
Stir and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rolled oats and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto a buttered baking sheet or waxed paper.
Cool before serving.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen small cookies.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Lightly grease mold with salad oil and turn to drain excess oil.
Mince tuna with eggs, olives and onions.
Soften gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Dissolve over hot water and add mayonnaise gradually, stirring constantly.
Fold into fish mixture.
Turn into mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: personal pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease one cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cutting board with flour.
Pull biscuits apart on the floured board.
Use rolling pin to roll out biscuits until it is 4-inches across.
Put on cookie sheet.
Repeat with all biscuits.
Add flour to board if starts to stick.
Spoon about 1 1/2 tablespoons pizza sauce onto each one.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese.
Add toppings.
Bake until crust is brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar	together;
add	eggs,
one at a time, mixing well after
each
addition.	Sift flour, salt and soda together and
add
alternately
with the buttermilk.
Mix red food coloring and cocoa	together
with	a fork and add to the creamed mixture.
Fold in flavoring and vinegar; mix well. Pour batter into 3 (9-inch)
cake pans which have been greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: wasper's nest cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box.
Add cake mix to pudding mixture and mix with mixer until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: santa fe casserole
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat until cooked through; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix, blending well.
In separate bowl, combine bouillon, flour and water.
Add to meat; bring to a boil to slightly thicken liquid.
Stir in sour cream and green chilies; blend thoroughly.
In lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, place 1/2 of chips.
Top with 1/2 beef mixture, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 of onions.
Layer again with remaining ingredients, ending with green onions.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: okra, tomato and corn
directions: Steam bacon, onion and pepper until it browns.
Cut up tomatoes and add to steamed bacon, onion and pepper.
Let it cool for about 10 minutes or longer.
Add okra and corn.
Season to your taste.
Let it cook until it gets tender.
It is very good over some rice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef slightly and put into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Drain liquid from beans and place beans on top of hamburger.
Put onion over the top of this and add undiluted soup. Top with Tater Tots and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Saute turkey and onion together in a large skillet.
Add all the other ingredients and cook at low heat about 40 minutes, or until rice is cooked.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together first 5 ingredients and stir in milk, oil and nuts.
Spread mixture into a 9-inch square pan.
In a small bowl, blend brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over all and bake for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in 2 cups water.
In another pan add bouillon cubes and 4 cups water.
Bring almost to a boil.
Make a roux of butter (flour 1/4 c.).
Stir into bouillon mixture, add broccoli, onion, water, cheese and stir until melted.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into 1/2-inch diameter balls. Brown in small amount of fat in a frying pan.
Place in large casserole.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Makes about 140 meatballs to be served with cocktail toothpicks.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cut cucumbers in small chunks and mash juice out. Mix cucumber chunks in cream cheese. Add garlic powder, seasoning salt and pepper to taste.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In top of double boiler, place cheese and milk, stirring over medium heat until smooth and simmering. In a large round casserole dish, spread evenly 1 can green beans. Pour 1/2 cheese sauce over beans. Spread evenly 1/2 onions; repeat. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: easy delicious lemon cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to package directions. Cook in two 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
Cool.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Stir half of cup of combined sauce and green chilies into browned meat and add 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup of onions.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 of remaining sauce on bottom of 10-inch round baking dish.
Stuff cooked shells with meat mixture and arrange in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello gelatin jigglers
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm or about 3 hours.
To remove, dip in warm about 15 seconds.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste with cocoa, water and food coloring.
Add to mixture.
Mix salt, vanilla and buttermilk; add alternately with flour to cream mixture.
Mix soda with vinegar and fold into mixture.
DO NOT beat.
Bake in (2) greased, floured pans.

title: potluck potato casserole
directions: Mix corn flakes with 1/4 cup of the melted butter.
Defrost potatoes.
Combine potatoes in large mixing bowl with the melted butter.
Add soup, salt, pepper and onions.
Blend thoroughly. Pour into greased casserole pan.
Cover with corn flake crumbs and butter.
Cook for 45 minutes on 350°.

title: fish foil bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Clean and rinse fish and allow to drain.
Mix together oleo, parsley, dill, chives, onion and lemon juice.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Lay fish on foil in single layer.
Spoon mixture over each piece of fish.
Cover with second piece of foil and seal the edges together.
Bake 20 minutes. Unwrap and remove to a hot platter.
Garnish with lemon slices and parsley (optional).
Serves 4.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add food coloring, salt, flour and milk.
Cream well.
Bake in pan sprayed with Pam at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain pork and beans.
Add cut up onions, eggs and pickles. Add mayonnaise and blend all together.

title: on cloud nine
directions: In a blender, mix water, orange juice, bananas and protein powder for 1 minute.
Add tofu and spirulina; mix for 1 minute, until blended well.
Makes 5 cups.

title: all-american apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Add apples and toss to mix.
Roll out pastry and line pie pan.
Trim off overhang.
Roll pastry for top, cut vents near center.
Add half the apples.
Pack well.
Dot with butter.
Add remaining apples.
Moisten rim with water.
Adjust top crust.
Leave 1/2-inch beyond edge and fold under seal and trim.
Brush with milk.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: orange sherbet mold
directions: This mix is a nonfat substitute for condensed cream soup in your favorite recipes.
You can also use it as a soup and add vegetables and/or meats of your choice.
Ingredients are listed for the equivalent of 8 cans or for 1 can.
Make the larger amount and store it in an airtight container.
Stir well before using.

title: 6 layer napoleon cake(torte)
directions: Chop, with a knife, the margarine and flour until lumps form. Add cold water, vinegar and salt.
Make dough; divide into 7 balls.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll each ball into a round crust (about size of medium pizza).
Place in 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes, until light golden brown.

title: peanut crunch
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch morsels in top of double boiler.
Add corn flakes and stir until coated.
Drop on waxed paper.
Yields approximately 50 small cookies.

title: candied sweet potatoes(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cut sweet potatoes into halves.
Mix water, butter, sugar and molasses or dark corn syrup.
Put in frying pan or heavy pot.
Add sweet potatoes.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is candied and potatoes are done.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Fix cheese and cream; beat until fluffy. Add mayonnaise or salad dressing, salt and orange juice. Makes 3/4 cup. Good over fruit salad.

title: ham and asparagus divine
directions: Slice ham 1/4-inch thick.
Cook asparagus until tender; drain. Alternate slices of ham and asparagus in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in milk and sour cream, stirring until sauce thickens.
Stir in cheese until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Spoon sauce over casserole. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until top is browned.
(I use canned asparagus.)

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Bake in buttered dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Follow cake mix directions.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Set other 1/2 batter aside.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While cake is cooling, pour Eagle Brand milk over caramels in medium size saucepan; melt over low heat.
Pour caramel mixture over baked cake, then pour other 1/2 batter over caramel layer.
Bake for another 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cake cool completely.

title: broccoli bake
directions: In pan, mix soup, milk, pepper, soy sauce, broccoli and 1/2 cup onions.
Bake
at 350° for 25 minutes; stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes; serve hot.

title: grandmother's cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in greased 3-quart casserole (or stuff 10 to 12 pound turkey).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: de ann's barbecue pork(oven-style)
directions: Marinade pork in a large bowl with barbecue sauce for 1 hour in refrigerator.
When ready to cook, heat oven to 350°.
Place pork in baking dish.
Add diced onion on top.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: five pounds of chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Combine sugar and evaporated milk in a buttered Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches a soft ball stage or candy thermometer registers 234°.
Pour over chocolate morsel mixture.
Beat at high speed with an electric mixer or wooden spoon until mixture thickens and begins to lose its gloss.
Stir in vanilla and chopped pecans.

title: barley pilaf
directions: Saute in electric skillet until brown.
Add mushrooms with juice.
Dissolve G. Washington seasoning in 3 cups water.
Turn down to boil and cook until done.

title: jean stapleton's nut fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
In large bowl, cream oleo and 1/4 cup powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup flour and baking powder.
Beat until well mixed.
Add remaining flour, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Dough should be stiff.
Stir in nuts.

title: tamale pie
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and garlic until brown.
Add tomato sauce, cheese soup, whole kernel corn, chili and green chili peppers.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix cornbread mix and make it thinner and pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 350° until brown.

title: banana nut cookies
directions: Sift flour mixture together 3 times.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg; mix well.
Add mashed bananas.
Add flour mixture, oats and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: big mama's biscuit pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole pan.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Bake for 25 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: hush babies
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruit.
Pour into a greased pie pan or a 9-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Serve immediately topped with fresh fruit.

title: white chili(lo-cal)
directions: In large saucepan, bring water to boil.
Stir in bouillon. Add the next 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle salt over mixture and let set overnight.
Drain real well.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Makes 8 pints.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve
strawberry
Jell-O
in
2 cups boiling water. Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas, diced.
Pour 1/2 in 8 x 12-inch
Pyrex
dish.
Let
chill
and jell in refrigerator. Keep other
half at room temperature.
When refrigerated part is firm, spread
cup of sour cream on top.
Then pour other half of Jell-O on and chill.

title: great banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions using 3 cups skim milk; fold in half of Cool Whip.
Reserve 6 wafers and 1 banana.
Slice remaining bananas.
Arrange a layer of wafers on bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Spread 1/4 pudding over wafers; top with banana slices.
Place wafers around sides of dish; continue layering wafers, pudding and bananas, ending with pudding.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Slice remaining banana. Garnish with banana slices, remaining 6 wafers and Cool Whip.

title: my favorite chili
directions: Brown meats, onion, garlic and green pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Can be frozen.

title: iced fresh tomato soup
directions: Cut tomatoes into eighths.
Force tomatoes, basil and onion through food mill, or whirl in blender and pour through a wire strainer.
Add chicken broth, sugar, salt, pepper and white wine; whip to blend.
Chill thoroughly.
Stir before serving.
Float peeled, cooked shrimp on top, or garnish with salted whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken curry
directions: Singe, wash, dry and cut up chicken.
Brown it in heated butter or oleo.
Mix in onion, Accent, salt, ketchup or tomato paste and boiling water.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Lift out chicken. Combine cornstarch, curry powder and cold water; stir into gravy. Cook, stirring constantly, until smoothly thickened.
Return chicken pieces to gravy.
Cover pan and simmer 15 minutes longer. Serve over rice.

title: great-grandma's sheepwagon carrot cake
directions: In medium saucepan mix first 8 ingredients.
Simmer over low heat 5 minutes.
Cover and set aside for 12 hours.
Next day add remaining ingredients. Pour mixture into 2 well-greased loaf pans or 1 tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 50 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar or top with a broiled frosting.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add egg, shortening, sugar and salt.
Gradually work in flour.
Let rise.
Punch down.
Cover and refrigerate or make out in rolls and let rise.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days if tightly covered.
It is best if kept 1 day in refrigerator.
Allow 2 to 3 hours to rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Can also be made into 3 loaves.

title: buttermilk cookie salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and instant pudding. Fold in Cool Whip. Add mandarin oranges (drained) and cookies (broken in pieces) when ready to serve.

title: pear-cherry cobbler
directions: Mix pears with juice, cherries with juice, cornstarch, 1/4 cup sugar and the nutmeg in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until it boils and thickens; boil 1 minute.
Pour fruit into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Keep hot in oven while preparing topping.
Mix baking mix, 1 tablespoon sugar, milk and oleo into soft dough.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fruit.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dynamites
directions: Simmer together for 4 hours, skimming any fat off the top. Serve in a hoagie roll.

title: white sauce
directions: In saucepan, gradually stir the milk into cornstarch.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.

title: bernie's easy meat loaf
directions: Mix undiluted vegetable soup, meat, egg and bread crumbs. Shape and place in roasting pan in oven.
Place uncooked bacon on meat loaf before placing in oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Enjoy.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or beat with mixer until mixed well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cool rise white bread
directions: Spoon flour into a 1 cup measuring cup; level off.
Set aside. Combine 1 cup flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Add hot tap water to bowl.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup more flour.
Beat at high for 1 minute until thick and elastic.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix cherry pie filling, pineapple, milk, marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts.
Cool and chill overnight.

title: short ribs with korean-style marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Ziploc bag. In it place the meat to be marinated.
Marinate overnight, turning bag occasionally.
Remove meat from marinade.
Place marinade in a saucepan and bring to a boil, reducing slightly.
Grill meat over charcoal, basting with marinade.
Grill scallions during last 4 to 5 minutes of cooking time.
Source:
Gourmet, August 1992.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with a variety of fresh vegetables.

title: summer salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
In a bowl, mix together the pepper, salad dressing, sugar, salt and vinegar. Blend well.
Stir in vegetables, ham and noodles. Refrigerate overnight.

title: barbary pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Add both ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: heart smart coleslaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard. Chill.
Just before serving, toss cabbage, green pepper and onion.
Moisten with dressing.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Mix the first four ingredients in a bowl and set aside.
Melt butter, cocoa and water and bring to a boil. Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased jelly roll pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix milk and flour, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Yields two pies.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: almond fruit punch
directions: Make jello as directed on package.
Add rest of ingredients, except ginger ale.
Mix thoroughly.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Sherbet may also be added when ready to serve.
Serves 25.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Shape into 4 burgers. The mixture may be somewhat crumbly.
Coat bottom of large skillet (nonstick) with margarine.
Add the burgers.
Preheat burner to medium-high.
Place pan with burgers on burner.
Cook for 7 to 8 minutes, until burgers form a nice brown crust.
Carefully flip, being certain to take up the brown crust when turning.
Reduce heat to medium and cook another 5 to 6 minutes.
Good served with white sauce with English peas added.
Contains 238 calories each.

title: lemon sauce(sauce for dessert)
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch; add the boiling water and a pinch of salt and boil until thick and clear.
Continue cooking over hot water for twenty minutes.
Beat in the butter, the lemon juice and nutmeg.
A grating of lemon rind may be added.
Great over Gingerbread Cake.

title: spaghetti loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing lightly, but thoroughly.
Form into a loaf.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: kiwi fruit daiquiri
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in electric blender; process until smooth.
Garnish with fruit slices.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Peel and boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Mash potatoes, then add all the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour with baking powder and spices and add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in mashed sweet potatoes, nuts, raisins and dates.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chicken on rice
directions: Mix soup with milk.
Add can of mushrooms and package of onion soup mix.
Put rice in oblong pan, then arrange chicken on top of rice.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Make sure soup mixture gets under chicken and the rice is wet with mixture.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 350°, then uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: stuffed baked peppers
directions: Remove stems and seeds from peppers.
Scald in boiling water until tender.
Dice onion and potato fine and cook in butter in a saucepan.
When they begin to get tender, add the mixed meat and bread crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper.
When this mixture is done, stuff the peppers with it.
Place stuffed peppers in baking dish; sprinkle with grated cheese and bake about 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine sugar, oil, butter, milk and eggs in large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Add dry ingredients and mix at low speed just until blended.
Fold in carrots, pecans and vanilla.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: low-fat garlic rosemary pork roast
directions: Untie roast and trim off fat.
Re-tie roast.
Rub garlic over surface.
Combine rosemary, chives and parsley.
Sprinkle evenly. Cover and chill 2 to 4 hours.
Place roast on a rack of broiler pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of roast.
Place roast in a 450° oven.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 160°.
Let roast stand 10 minutes.
Remove string and slice diagonally across grain.

title: baked pretzels
directions: Mix flour, milk, butter, baking powder, sugar and salt to a soft dough.
Gently knead on a floured surface into a smooth ball, adding small amounts of flour to dough, if necessary.
Take walnut size pieces of dough and roll into long strips, 12 to 15-inches long by 1/4-inch thick.
Twist each strip into pretzel shape and place seam side down on a greased cookie sheet. Brush pretzels with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden.

title: new york style cheesecake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crushed graham crackers and sugar. Press into bottom of spring-form pan base.

title: low-fat tijuana bean dip
directions: Microwave Directions:
In a 1 1/2-quart dish, combine beans, cheese, green onions and jalapeno peppers.
Cover with a piece of wax paper.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato, salsa and lemon juice.
Serve warm with Low-fat Tortilla Chips.
Makes about 12 (1/4-cup) servings.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and soak overnight.
Bag in Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: paradiddle pound cake
directions: Sift cake mix, flour and pudding mix into mixing bowl.
Add sugar.
Beat eggs and add to bowl along with the lemon extract flavoring, the milk and the oil.
Mix until consistent.
Pour into Bundt pan and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts) in heavy saucepan.
Boil to hard ball stage.
Beat; add nuts.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: left over turkey
directions: Bake patty shells as directed.
Cook green pepper in butter until tender. Blend in soup and milk; add turkey, pimento and almonds. Heat and stir now and then. Add sherry if desired. Serve in patty shells.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add butter, flour, cocoa, vanilla, coconut and walnuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased square pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
While hot, pour Marshmallow Creme over cake.

title: company chicken-rice casserole
directions: Grease a 10 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle the rice on the bottom.
Arrange the chicken pieces on top of the rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over the chicken.
Mix together the cans of soup and milk until smooth and pour over the chicken and rice.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: poached chicken breasts in wine
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thick; set aside.
Combine wine and next 5 ingredients in large skillet; bring to boil over high heat. Arrange chicken in a single layer in skillet; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to serving dish; keep warm.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir into skillet and bring mixture to a boil.
Boil one minute, stirring constantly.
Pour over chicken.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in a large pan and boil for 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder and mix thoroughly.
Roll 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut out cookies in any shape.
Bake in oven at 375° to 400° on ungreased cookie sheet. Allow 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: seven-star fudge cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in melted chocolate.
I use 18 heaping teaspoonfuls cocoa mixed with 6 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Pour batter into 3 (8-inch) layer pans.
Bake in a moderate oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
This is a good moist cake.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix together the oil, sugar, oleo, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, cocoa, baking soda and cinnamon and add to the first mixture.
Mix together the zucchini and nuts and add.
Place in a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan and
sprinkle the chocolate bits over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40-45 minutes.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into ungreased 8-inch square baking pan. Stir in almond extract. Combine flour, brown sugar and cinnamon in medium bowl; mix well. Add butter. Stir with fork until mixture is crumbly. Stir in walnuts and coconut. Sprinkle mixture over cherry pie filling. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden on top and filling is bubbly. Serve warm or at room temperature. If desired, top with ice cream or whipped cream. Easy and Excellent! Serves 6.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter.
Add cheese, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Drizzle over mixed Chex, pretzels, Cheez-Its and nuts.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk all at once, stir until dough follows fork around bowl.

title: cool blueberry salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine 1 pint of blueberries, orange juice and sugar; bring to a boil and cool.
In another saucepan, dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water, then add cold water and stir.
Let cool.
Add blackberry brandy.
Mix lemon jello and brandy mixture with partially cooked blueberries, sour cream, lemon rind and spices.
Stir in remaining blueberries.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Unmold and serve with sour cream.

title: all around family cake westerner
directions: Have eggs and butter at room temperature.
Cream butter; add Imperial 10x powdered sugar.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Sift flour 3 times; add gradually to batter.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake in 10-inch greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 4 minutes, then invert pan.
Delicious served plain with Imperial 10x powdered sugar sprinkled lightly into ridges on top of cake.
Or top with ice cream, fruit, whipped cream or dessert sauce.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make a sauce of mayo, vinegar and sugar.
Mix other ingredients in large bowl.
Toss in sauce.
Serve cold.

title: dieter's meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Shape into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: borscht(beet soup)
directions: Saute sausage, onion, garlic and carrot in olive oil.
Add broth, beets, cabbage, tomato, sugar, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine vinegar, beet juice and cornstarch and add to broth mixture.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Serve with 1 to 2 tablespoons sour cream on top.

title: family nachos
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Spread bean dip to cover bottom of 12-inch pizza pan. Sprinkle with cheese; top with meat then chilies.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes.
Around edge of pan arrange a border of lettuce, then tomatoes and onions, then tortilla chips.
Place mound of guacamole topped with sour cream in center.
Makes 4 servings.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add seasoning and tomato sauce. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix onion, cream cheese and sour cream.
In a buttered baking dish, layer meat, noodles, meat and cream cheese mixture until all is used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and Karo and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix.
Stir this over corn flakes.
Drop cookies on wax paper.

title: four bean salad
directions: Combine beans in a large bowl.
In a quart jar, combine the remaining ingredients.
Cover and shake together thoroughly.
Pour over beans.
Mix together gently.
Chill overnight or for several hours.
Add to tossed salads or use as a side dish.

title: healthy wheat bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix last 2 ingredients.
Add to others.
Grease 1 loaf pan.
Top with sunflower seeds.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: cranberry walnut cheesecake pie
directions: Pour milk in a large bowl.
Add pudding mixes and lemon peel. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Gently stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture on bottom of crust. Spread 1/2 of the cranberry sauce over pudding mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 of the walnuts.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Garnish with remaining cranberry sauce, whipped topping and walnuts.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, margarine and Rice Krispies well. Form into small balls and place on waxed paper.
Melt wax and chocolate together.
(You may want to use a little less wax and a little more chocolate.)
Dip balls into chocolate and set on waxed paper to cool.
Yields 24 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil in heavy pan margarine, water and cocoa. Combine remaining cake ingredients in bowl and add margarine mixture.
Pour into greased 11 x 17-inch pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: wine meat balls
directions: In
saucepan, combine sugar, tomato sauce, lemon juice, garlic salt
and
wine.
Simmer until sauce is thick, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Combine the shredded potato, meat, onion, egg and salt. Shape
into
small	balls.	Bake in 350° oven until done and lightly
browned.
Drain off fat and pour sauce over all.

title: jeannette's pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on top of cold water.
Beat egg yolks in top of double boiler pan (or improvised one); apply no heat yet (use rotary beater).
Add brown sugar, milk, spices, pumpkin and gelatin.
Cook, stirring constantly until slightly thickened. Remove from double boiler, cool until somewhat thick.
Beat egg whites and sugar; fold into pumpkin mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Put whipped something on top before serving.

title: jalapeno cheese corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake 25 minutes at 425° until done.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Divide into 2 bowls.
Take half of cake batter, 1 stick melted margarine and half can milk. Mix well and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Wash and drain chicken. Place in shallow pan, skin side up. Mix Coke and catsup; add salt and pepper and pour over chicken. Cover and cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spinach-ham rolls
directions: Combine cottage cheese and sour cream in container of an electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Combine sour cream mixture and next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon 1/4 cup mixture on each slice of ham.
Roll up and place seam side down in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with Cheese Sauce. Sprinkle with paprika.
Garnish with onion tops and parsley. Yields 12 servings.

title: caramel walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, egg and oleo to crumbs.
Add walnuts.
Reserve 2 cups of crumbs; press remaining mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In a saucepan, melt 24 Kraft caramels and 1/4 cup oleo and a 14 ounce can sweetened condensed Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over baked crust; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until beginning to bubble.
Cool, cut and store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix well and shape into rounded balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven. Place candy Kisses on top. Bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Can use as much of batter as wanted and bake in an oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in paper-lined muffin tins.
Can refrigerate leftover batter until next time.

title: mint juleps
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Place mint leaves in 1-quart container.
Pour cooled syrup over mint leaves and refrigerate at least 12 hours, but no more than 24 hours.
Cover tightly.

title: cinnamon spice cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: polish mistake
directions: Brown sausage and meat separately and drain well.
Mix well with remaining ingredients until cheese melts.
Refrigerate.
After chilled, spread on rye bread and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
This can also be heated and served with crackers or party bread.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Lightly butter 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and line bottom of pan with layer of graham crackers.
Fill in empty spaces with crackers, too.
Prepare instant pudding according to directions, but use only 3 cups of half and half.
Fold pudding into thawed Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mixture
over graham crackers.
Place another layer of crackers on top of pudding, then pour other 1/2 of mixture.
Place another layer of graham crackers on top. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Spread icing on top layer of crackers and refrigerate another 2 hours.

title: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugars until creamy; add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt pauline's chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar together.
Layer the first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Spread mixture over to sides of bowl to seal well.
Cover and chill.
This is better if made the night before.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in pan with chopped onion.
Drain off grease.
Put in baking dish with rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: olive spread
directions: Dissolve minced onion with sherry.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Blend butter, shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time, with milk and flavoring.
Alternate.
Add eggs, beating after each one.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test and bake longer if needed.

title: beef nachos casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, salad dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 of the meat mixture, chips and cheese into 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole(easy)
directions: Cook noodles in
boiling
water 20 minutes; drain.
Add chicken and corn flakes.
Make sauce with milk, flour, butter, green pepper and salt.
Add mushroom soup.	Pour over noodles. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish cheese cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill milk good.
Whip until it is stiff.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sugar, lemon juice and grated rind.
Blend well and chill until slightly
jelled.
Whip jello mixture lightly and add to whipped milk.
Blend well.
Line oblong baking dish with crushed graham crackers.
Pour jello mixture into graham cracker crust.
To garnish, sprinkle light layer of crushed graham cracker crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy.
Beat in egg and sugar substitute.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together; add to shortening mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields about 34 cookies.

title: poor man cinnamon rolls
directions: Butter sliced bread and cut in half.
Sprinkle halves with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll pieces up and place in a muffin pan. Coat tops with butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 10 Cinnamon Rolls.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray pie pan with Pam cooking spray.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into two round cake pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake and frost.

title: cherry cheesecake dessert
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, butter and powdered sugar in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs; pour over crust.
Bake at 320° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Pour cherry pie filling over top and garnish with Cool Whip. Sprinkle one tablespoon of crumb mix on top.

title: macaroon cookie bars
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl until mixture is well blended. Mixture may be crumbly.
Press evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: johnny musette
directions: Mix bell pepper, celery, onion, beef, tomato paste, sauce, and soup with water, mushrooms. and garlic.
Simmer to thicken. Add cooked and drained macaroni.
Pour into covered casserole. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 250°, covered the last 15 minutes.

title: grandma's chicken vichyssoise
directions: Brown chicken breasts in butter along with chopped onion and garlic.
Put it in a casserole.
Heat both cans of vichyssoise soup, 1/2 cup shredded cheese, white wine, rosemary and thyme until cheese is melted.
Pour mixture over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded cheese over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: will's "is it any good?" chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except kidney beans.
Simmer for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Add kidney beans and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Add tomato juice if chili is too thick.
Do not use cheaper brands of sauce or juice.

title: glowing jack-o'-lantern cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter or oleo and shortening with electric mixer about 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy. Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, beating well.
Cover; chill for about 3 hours. Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover cookie sheets with foil; divide dough in half and chill 1/2.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out other half so it is 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 4 to 5-inch circles; place 2-inches apart on cookie sheets.
Repeat with remaining dough.
With sharp knife, cut eyes, mouth and nose out of each circle.
Fill holes with cracked candy.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are light brown on edge.
Let cool on foil for 10 minutes.
Peel off foil; cool on racks.
Makes 24 to 36 cookies.

title: apple relish
directions: Cook slowly for 45 minutes and put in 3 pint jars.

title: caramel filling for cake
directions: Mix sugar and whipping cream. Bring to a boil. Stir and boil constantly until of spreading consistency. Remove from heat and beat until cool a little.
Add salt and a few drops flavoring. Spread between layers and on top of cake.
Will frost 3 or 4 layer cake or sheet cake.

title: clam & spinach lasagna
directions: 1. Cook noodles and set aside.
Drain clams and reserve juice. 2. In a 2-3 qt pan melt butter over medium heat.
Add flour stirring until bubbly.
Gradually stir in reserved & bottle of clam juice.
Continue cooking until it thick ens, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. 3. Stir in clams, garlic, herbs, parsley, and lemon juice.
Season top with pepper. 4. Line 9 x 13 baking dish with 1/3 of noodles.
Spoon cottage cheese evenly over noodles. Top with 1/3 sauce.
Add second layer of noodles. 5. Squeeze all liquid out of spinach and arrange over noodles.
Cover with 1/2 of jack cheese.
Cover with 1/2 remaining sauce, top with noodles, cheese, and sauce.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Soak
mushrooms in warm water 30 minutes.
Slice thinly and discard
tough
stems and liquid.
Spray 3 quart saucepan with nonstick
spray.
Lightly
saute
pork over medium heat. Add broth, mushrooms, bamboo shoots, onions, vinegar, crushed red pepper flakes and soy sauce.
Stirring occasionally, bring to boil
over medium heat and boil 10 minutes.
Stir together cornstarch	and
water
until smooth.
Add to soup.
Stir constantly,
bring	to
a
boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute. Slowly
stir
in egg in fine stream.
Sprinkle with sesame oil to taste.
May
add tofu in small cubes and salad size shrimp. Fresh mushrooms may be substituted for dried variety.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken, soups, vegetables and garlic salt in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pinky's enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Brown flour over low burner.
Add chili powder, garlic powder and onions.
Add water, slowly, stirring, and let boil.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy, about 3 minutes. Beat in flour and sugars until well blended.
Beat in butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until knife comes out clean and top is golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: italian chili
directions: *About 3 medium-sized squash, do not use large zucchini, too many seeds and the peel gets hard when cooked.

title: easy deep dish pasta
directions: Brown meat.
Add garlic, onions, sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni; rinse in cold water.

title: banana smash punch
directions: In a large pan, boil the water and sugar until mix is dissolved.
Cool.
Mix juices with sugar water and bananas.
Pour into 2 equal measure containers to freeze. Freeze overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; add all ingredients. Marinate overnight.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Chop finely onion, garlic, celery and bell pepper and saute in olive oil.
Crumble hamburger in sauteed vegetables and stir until brown.
Add cream of chicken soup and 3/4 can of water.
Stir and let thicken (about 5 minutes).
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add next flour ingredients and mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: clams casino dip
directions: Fry bacon; drain fat.
Chop bacon.
Saute pepper and celery. Add onion and chopped bacon; continue cooking until onion is translucent.
Crumble crackers.
Melt butter.
Add butter to crackers.
Add crumb mixture to vegetables in skillet.
Add pimento, clams and clam juice; season with salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice and hot sauce (2 to 3 drops).
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish with crackers.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour.
Add nuts and potato chips.
Mix well.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch, salt and 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Stir in remaining milk.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes or until thickened.
Stir occasionally the last half of cooking.
Beat a little of the hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks; then add the egg yolk mixture to the remaining hot mixture. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until thickened.
Blend in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into cooled, baked pastry shell.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt butter.
Add crackers and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Mix well. Line the bottom of a baking dish.

title: peas 'n bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding cheese last.
Pour into greased oblong baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sally lund
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks, salt and flour alternating with milk that has been heated until lukewarm and mixed with yeast.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into a well-greased tube pan in which it is to be baked and let stand until double its bulk (2 1/2 to 3 hours).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in oven set at 375°.
When golden brown and tests done, remove from oven and turn onto serving plate.
Cut into wedges and butter while hot or serve with pitcher of melted butter.
Leftover Sally Lund is delicious toasted.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cook round steaks over medium heat in oil and Worcestershire sauce.
Remove meat and add soups and soy sauce.
Heat to smooth consistency.
Add steak and rice mix.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle with cheese and green onions.
Cover and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put potatoes in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Lay pork chops on top.
Mix 2 cans of soup together.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: western skillet rice
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat, stirring frequently.
Stir in onion soup mix, water, rice, tomatoes and peas. Simmer covered for 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Top with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tasty turkey pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix Miracle Whip, flour, bouillon and pepper in saucepan.
Gradually add milk.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Add turkey and mixed vegetables.
Cook until heated through.
Spoon into 8-inch square baking dish.
Open can of crescent rolls, use 2 rectangles to form square piece of flat dough.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
Arrange in lattice design over turkey mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and shape into balls. Cook in a shallow baking pan at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and cream cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese; drain can of shrimp.
Chop green onions; mix together well with a fork.
Add a dash of Worcestershire sauce; mix again.
Even better if made several hours ahead.
Serve on "Club" crackers.
So yummy it's hard to stop eating!

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Combine; chill or may be served warm with crackers or tostados.

title: orange cake
directions: Grind whole orange and raisins.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add and blend well one egg at a time.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Dissolve soda in hot water, add to milk.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with milk.
Do not beat, just stir to mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Add orange and raisins.
Bake in deep pans at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Can be made in layers or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until tests done.

title: paw paw's old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until sugar is fairly well dissolved.
Add eggs, one at a time, while continuing to beat.
Add vanilla.
Fold in flour.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Put waxed paper in bottom of pan.
Pour mix into pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: swiss turkey quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes, then remove from the oven. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In a medium bowl, toss cheese with flour and bouillon. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until set, topping with French fried onion rings during the last 10 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine according to directions.
Rinse and drain.
Mix all the ingredients together and chill.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and mix.
Add syrup and salt; beat. Add eggs.
Stir in coconut and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: make-believe apple pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cinnamon to a boil.
Add crushed crackers and brown sugar.
When thick, take off heat and add cream of tartar.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Top with a little butter, add top crust, and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
and
drain
broccoli
according to package directions. Beat
egg;
add
mayonnaise,
onions,
soup and grated cheese. Carefully add the broccoli to the sauce and pour into a
buttered casserole
dish.
Top with crushed cracker cheese bits.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
I double the recipe.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix room temperature cream cheese and peanut butter until fluffy.
Mix powdered sugar and Cool Whip, then add to creamed mixture.
Pour into the 2 crusts.
May serve frozen or from refrigerator.

title: chocolate macadamia muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine over hot (not boiling) water, semi-sweet morsels and butter.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts to coat well.
Make a well in the center of flour mixture.
In a small bowl, combine melted morsels, sour cream, corn syrup and egg until blended.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until just moistened.
Spoon into paper-lined muffin pans, filling each about 3/4 full.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely or serve warm.
Makes about 15 muffins.

title: coconut mist cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure;
add baking powder and salt. Sift 3
times.
Cream
butter;
add
sugar
gradually.
Cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well. Add
flour alternately
with
milk.
Add vanilla and coconut. Fold
quickly and
thoroughly
the egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy potato sticks
directions: Peel potatoes or wash skins thoroughly.
Cut lengthwise into quarters.
Cut each quarter into thirds.
Coat potatoes with margarine.
Combine crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Roll potatoes in mixture.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes and cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and milk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Refrigerate until thickened. Stir in strawberries.
Spoon over cream cheese. Chill for 3 hours. Cut into squares.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with carrots, celery, cauliflower, radishes, onions, broccoli, cucumbers and peppers.

title: onion and pepper steak
directions: Cook green peppers and onions in hot oil. Remove and set aside. Add meat and brown. Then add soup, gravy mix and 2 cans of water. Simmer until tender. Add cooked peppers and onions. Serve over rice.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix well.
Roll dough out to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Fry carefully in hot oil or until they float. This just takes a few minutes.
Drain well.
Roll in sugar or cinnamon/sugar mixture while warm.
Enjoy!

title: eggs for brunch
directions: Combine croutons and cheese.
Spread in a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, mustard, green onion and pepper.
Pour over croutons.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Mix ingredients; refrigerate.
Serve with fruit or vegetables.

title: steak in a brown bag
directions: Make a paste of garlic, oil, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; spread mixture over steak on all sides.
Press crumbs firmly on both sides of steak.
Place steak in a brown bag and close with a skewer.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes for rare (approximately 15 minutes per pound).

title: italian sausage with mostaccioli
directions: In a large saucepan, brown sausage; pour off fat. Add onion, pepper and seasonings.
Stir until tender.
Add pasta sauce and Parmesan cheese. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook mostaccioli. Toss with olive oil.
Serve with spaghetti sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cooked cornmeal mush
directions: Mix corn meal, cold water and salt. Stir slowly, pour corn meal mixture into boiling water in saucepan.
Cook and stir until thick. Lower heat.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring as needed to keep from sticking.

title: freezer cake
directions: Cut cake once horizontally.
Put ice cream or sherbet in between the layers.
Place top layer on ice cream.
Fill center with hole with ice cream.
Use Cool Whip to ice the outside and top of cake.

title: glorious pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; blend. Add flour gradually.
Pour into a buttered, lightly floured 10-inch tube pan.

Bake in a 325° gas oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool in pan about 10 minutes before removing to cake rack. Serve with fresh fruit and whipped cream.

title: raw vegie salad
directions: Mix each chopped, salted vegetable separately with enough mayonnaise to bind.
On a leaf of lettuce, place a mound of carrots.
Place a mound of cabbage on carrots and on top of that, a mound of green peppers.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serve with French dressing or mayonnaise.

title: orange candied carrots
directions: Place 1-inch of water and carrots in a skillet. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: strawberry filling
directions: Boil slowly until changes color.
Add 1 large box strawberry jello.
Stir until thickened slightly more.
Refrigerate until thick.
Add strawberries.
Pour into packed crust.
Cool Whip topping, if desired.

title: velveeta casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat.
Drain grease from hamburger meat.
Add soups and then add Velveeta cheese.
Let cheese melt.
Pour over Doritos in a pan and then put Doritos on top.
Let cool, then serve.

title: the best-ever cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large saucepan, heat milk, the 1/3 cup margarine or butter, the 1/3 cup sugar and salt just until warm (120° to 130°) and margarine is almost melted, stirring constantly.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Using a wooden spoon, stir in as much of the remaining 2 1/4 to 2 3/4 cups flour as you can.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately soft dough that is smooth and elastic (3 to 5 minutes total).
Shape into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until double (about 1 hour).

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix carrots, oil, eggs and sugar.
Add pecans.
Sift in salt, cinnamon and flour. Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: trebie's jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, pepper, celery, garlic and sausage in large pan. Pour off any drippings.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, thyme, bay leaf, salt, cayenne, water and rice.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Clean and devein shrimp while other is cooking.
Add shrimp last 10 minutes.
May need more water and seasoning.
May use chicken instead of, or with shrimp.
Serve with creole seasoning to taste.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed and garlic powder.
Finely chop green pepper, broccoli and carrots.
Spread roll dough on cookie sheet and bake until slightly brown.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Sprinkle with veggies.

title: spice pickles
directions: Cut pickles into small chunks.
Soak pickles in boiling water and coarse salt (about a handful) for 2 hours.
Drain.
Put all ingredients except pickles in kettle.
Bring to a boil and add pickles.
Simmer a few minutes until juice turns yellow.
Put in jars.
Makes about 5 or 6 quarts.

title: vodka sauce
directions: Simmer the first six ingredients for 15 minutes.
Add light cream to make a pink color (individual's choice of color).
Simmer another five minutes.
Serve over pasta of your choice.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add Ro-Tel, taco sauce and both soups; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for about 30 minutes.
Put serving of chips on each plate.
Pour hamburger mixture over chips; top with cheese.
(Great for campouts!)

title: chiperoo bars
directions: Melt shortening.
Stir in brown sugar.
Mix well and cool. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
To shortening mixture, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts. Spread in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Or for thicker bars, use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 50 minutes.
When almost cool, cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: my own cookies
directions: Cream the butter with sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add half of the nuts.
Blend in flour and remaining nuts. Shape into small ovals on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: cinnamon square
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
With pastry blender, cut in butter.
Mix milk and vanilla.
With fork, beat in egg.

title: fudge-full peanut butter bars
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl.
Stir by hand until dough holds together.
Press about 1/2 or 2/3 dough into the bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Reserve rest of dough for top filling.
In heavy pan, combine chips, milk and butter.
Melt and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add frosting.
Pour over dough and spread.
Cover with rest of dough.
Roll on wax paper to make it easier for the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler or microwave.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill well before cutting (will not cut into even pieces).
Very much like Reese's.

title: artichoke spread for crackers
directions: Mix the cheese and mayo.
Squeeze water from the artichokes completely.
Mix all together and put into a quiche pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry spinach(popeye's favorite)
directions: Heat oil in wok or stir-fry pan.
When hot, add garlic and salt.
Stir until fragrant (not browned) and add spinach.
Keep stirring and when spinach begins to wilt, add sugar.
Continue to stir until well wilted (around 1 to 2 minutes).
Spread flat on shallow platter and sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Serve immediately.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine in bowl.
Set aside.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over corn meal.
Stir until cool to keep from lumping.
Add butter and egg yolks.
Stir until egg yolks are thoroughly blended in.
Stir in buttermilk. Blend in salt, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Beat egg whites only until stiff enough to hold soft peaks.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until set.
Serve hot with butter.

title: tammie's chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Combine ingredients and let simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a heavy saucepan, saute onion, garlic and kielbasa for 4 to 5 minutes.
Heat chicken broth for 5 minutes; add to sausage mixture.
Add lentils, tomato juice, white wine, rosemary or basil and grated carrots.
Cook for 1 hour on low simmer.
In the last 20 minutes of cooking, add diced potatoes and spinach.
Add Tabasco to taste; add salt and pepper.
Just before serving, sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.

title: applesauce raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly. Stir in applesauce.
Mix dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: sherry delight
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar.
Add sherry.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add whipped cream.
Make crust of vanilla wafer crumbs on bottom and top of mixture.
Freeze slightly, if desired.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Prepare enchilada sauce mix according to directions on package.
Drain ground beef and mix 1/2 of sauce mix.
Place meat, about 3 tablespoons, on each tortilla. Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Add about 1 teaspoon of chopped onion on each, roll and place in large casserole pan.
Continue until you run out of meat mixture.
Using ladle, pour remaining sauce mix over enchiladas.
Cover well; sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
