Place in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: corn bread dressing with oysters
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in enough broth until the mixture is very wet.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs. Taste to see if you need more seasonings. Then add eggs and mix well. Pour into pan and bake at 400 until top is browned.

title: quick vegetable medley
directions: In large skillet, saute stewed tomatoes and fresh vegetables until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Refrigerate overnight. Good with fresh vegetables or corn chips.

title: drop oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil; stir 2 minutes.
Take off stove burner.
Add 3 cups quick oats and 1/2 cup crunchy peanut butter. Drop on buttered wax paper after mixing well.

title: caramel walnut cake
directions: Melt butter or oleo.
Bring to boil with brown sugar and light corn syrup.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch square cake pan.
Arrange chopped walnuts over mixture.
Top with cake batter made as directed on package.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Invert immediately, leaving pan over cake 1 minute.
Especially good served warm.
Top with whipped cream, cherry if desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook pasta and drain; brown hamburger and onions. Cook until done. Add tomato soup and ketchup; stir. Place in baking dish and cover with Velveeta cheese.

title: basque corn bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups lukewarm water, yeast and flour and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
In another large bowl, combine cornmeal, salt and 2 cups hot water; stir until water is completely absorbed.
Cover and let soften at room temperature 1 hour.
Stir down yeast mixture, then stir in cornmeal mixture and blend thoroughly.
(Dough will be liquid and batter-like.)
Cover and let rise 2 hours.
(Dough will be bubbly and will rise only slightly.)
Stir down dough and spoon into 2 well-buttered 8-inch round cake pans, filling them about 3/4 full. Cover and let rise 2 hours.
(Dough will rise only slightly.)
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until top is a pale golden brown.
Cool on racks.
Heat 5 minutes just before serving. Makes 2 loaves.
May be frozen up to 3 months.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients except potato chips or corn flakes.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips or corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Make dark roux; add onions, garlic, parsley and shrimp.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add water and seasonings; simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour and serve over rice.

title: one pan cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 15-inch pan (cover sides).
Add ingredients in order given.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cook broccoli and carrots about 2 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Mix cornstarch, salt, sugar, soy sauce and sherry; set aside.
Add oil to wok or pan over high heat and stir-fry broccoli, carrots and onions until crisp and tender.
Remove from wok.
Add beef and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove beef.

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
In a large saucepan, place sugar, milk and oleo.
Bring these to boil; boil for 9 minutes.
Pour over Hershey bar mixture and stir until chips are melted, then pour in buttered pan.
Yield:
5 pounds of fudge.

title: peach bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add peach preserves and sour cream.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans or 3 to 4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes. Stir in parsley or parsley flakes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano leaves.
Combine eggs and cheese.
Stir into zucchini mixture.
Separate dinner rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan; press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is set.
(Cover crust with foil during last 10 minutes of baking.)
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Stir sugar, chocolate, corn syrup and milk until sugar dissolves then cook slowly without stirring to 238° (soft ball). Add butter.
Remove from heat.
When lukewarm (240°, about 25 minutes, add vanilla.
Beat.
Ices double layer cake.

title: coconut refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Put by spoonfuls on cookie sheet or roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done, depending upon size of cookies.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a large bowl and mix together thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: virg's favorite meat loaf
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Shape mixture in a loaf pan.
Spread 2 or 3 tablespoons of ketchup on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.

Drain the blueberries and pineapple and measure the liquid; add enough water to make 1 cup. Add the gelatin mixture; stir in the blueberries and pineapple. Pour in a 2-quart flat pan and put in the refrigerator until firm. Blend the softened cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla; spread over the congealed salad.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack into three greased 4 x 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a moderate 350° oven. Serves 25.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt 6 ounces butterscotch chips with 1/2 cup peanut butter in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring until blended.
Stir in 4 cups Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill. Stir over hot water chocolate chips, powdered sugar, butter and water until melted and blended.
Spread over chilled mixture.
(Do not chill after adding chocolate layer.)
Melt the rest of the butterscotch chips and peanut butter; stir rest of Rice Krispies and spread over chocolate layer (do this as quickly as possible after spreading chocolate).
Press lightly.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: apple snack cake
directions: You will need a large bowl.
Mix together vegetable oil, eggs and sugar.
Beat medium speed until mixed well.
Put dry ingredients in a separate bowl (flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon).
Then mix dry ingredients into the large bowl mix well by hand.
Then add apples and nuts.
Spray pan with Bakers Joy or cooking spray.
Bake in square pan 9 x 13 for 40 minutes or 2 small pans for 50 minutes.
Bake less time.
Cake tester to check if the cake is done.

title: scrumptious cheesecake
directions: Beat in each ingredient in order as listed until smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Turn oven off and leave pan in oven with door cracked for 2 hours. Refrigerate. Top with strawberry, blueberry, cherry or apricot pie filling.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Place cheese in a double boiler top.
Cook over boiling water until cheese is melted.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, until sauce is smooth. Add Tabasco sauce and mustard. Blend thoroughly.
Yields 2 cups.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Put shells in boiling water (20 minutes).
Meanwhile, clean spinach.
Remove stems and place in tightly lidded pan (do not add water).
Cook on low to medium heat.
Heat until limp.
Chop. Slice mushrooms and onions.
Saute in 1 tablespoon corn oil.
Add garlic while sauteing.
Add tomato sauce and remainder of spices.
Simmer until everything else is ready.
(Be creative with the spices, do your own thing.)
Combine chopped spinach, Ricotta and Parmesan.
Mix well.
Drain shells.
Lightly oil pan.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture.
When finished, cover with tomato sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Feeds about 4 people as an entree.

title: aunt marian's hershey bar pie
directions: Break bar into pieces.
Melt chocolate with milk until smooth. Add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Cool completely.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Cover.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped topping or cherry pie filling.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: In a large glass bowl, heat crumbled ground meat 2 to 3 minutes on High until browned.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine Ricotta cheese, egg and pepper.
Spray oblong baking dish with nonstick spray.
Spoon 1/2 cup of sauce into dish, then alternately layer noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and sauce, making 2 layers.
Heat, covered, for 8 minutes on High.
Continue cooking on power level 5 an additional 30 to 32 minutes until noodles are tender.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand, covered, for 15 minutes before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients into saucepan; cook until spins thread from spoon.
Add the raw peanuts; cook until golden brown or until peanuts start popping.
Remove from heat.
Add the soda and pinch of salt; stir until mixed well.
Pour very thinly on greased cookie sheet.

title: almond delight
directions: Crust Topping:
Mix together, brown sugar, sliced almonds, coconut, flour and mix well with stick of melted butter.
Bake in large pan for 45 mins. at 325.
Stir often while baking to keep from burning.
While this mixture is cooling, make the filling...mix pudding with milk and add the cool whip.
Using a 9 1/2x13 pan, put a layer of crust mixture on the bottom, then a layer of pudding, another layer of crust, then another layer of pudding, top with crust mixture.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together nuts, sugar, Karo and salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place in microwave and cook on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Return to microwave and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool for 30 to 60 minutes.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: jo cunningham's shrimp-pineapple quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust and chill in 10-inch deep pie pan.
Layer bottom with shrimp, pineapple and water chestnuts, and mixture of Mozzarella, ginger, sugar, salt and flour.
Mix together cream and eggs and pour on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy fruit dip(low fat dip recipe)
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Has 11 calories per tablespoon, if made with sugar-free pudding: 16 calories per tablespoon, if make with regular pudding mix.
Zero fat grams.

title: microwave double decker fudge
directions: In
a
2-cup glass measuring cup, combine peanut butter chips and
cup condensed milk.
Cook on High about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes in microwave, stirring halfway to blend.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon
vanilla
until
mixture is smooth.
Spread into 8-inch square
foil-lined	pan.
Combine
remaining condensed milk and chocolate chips; repeat procedure as before.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until smooth and spread on top of peanut butter mixture. Chill
for	2
hours or until firm, then turn out and
peel off foil.
Cut into squares.
Store, covered, in fridge.

title: shiny finger paint
directions: Mix together; use as you would any other finger paint.
Dries glossy.

title: microwave tortilla pizza
directions: Place tortilla between two sheets paper towel (pierce with fork first).
Microwave on High 1 minute or until barely crisp.
Place on paper plate lined with paper towel.
Spread with sauce. Sprinkle with mushrooms, onions, cheeses and oregano.
Microwave on Medium-high 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Cook for 1 minute.
After boiling, add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Spoon out onto wax paper.

title: teriyaki fish fillets
directions: Measure 2 tablespoons of juice from pineapple can; mix with garlic, slivered ginger, onion, 3 teaspoons of teriyaki sauce and vinegar.
Arrange fish in shallow dish.
Pour marinade over fish. Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Arrange fish on greased broiler rack. Brush with marinade.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: jumbles - m&m's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugars until fluffy; add egg.
Combine flour and soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's, raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes. Cool 2 to 3 minutes before taking off cookie sheets.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 32 cookies.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour and coconut milk alternately, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites that have been beaten.
Bake in 3 large cake pans at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread with Seven Minute Icing; sprinkle with fresh grated coconut.

title: self-crust pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, put the egg whites and pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir in slowly 1 cup water.
Mix well. Pour in sprayed 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 8; 135 calories per serving and trace of fat.

title: surprise salad(aka green stuff)
directions: Set jello with boiling water and pineapple juice.
When set, beat in cream cheese, milk, carrot, pineapple and sugar.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar together in medium bowl. Blend well.
Roll into balls.
Roll in sugar.

title: salmon patties
directions: Grease pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Patty out and fry.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes (sliced) in water.
Add sliced onion and cook until color changes in water.
Pour water off.
Put in dish layer of potato and onion.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on each layer. Heat soup and water.
Pour over.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put cheese on top and melt.

title: freezer ice cream dessert
directions: Mix together all ingredients except ice cream.
Use half of the mixture for bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Soften the ice cream. Spread on crumbs. Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze and keep in freezer until ready to serve.
When serving, top with small amount of cherry, blueberry or other pie filling.

title: copper carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just barely done.
Mix soup and seasonings; pour over carrots and other vegetables.
Marinate overnight.

title: steve's macaroni salad
directions: Cook the macaroni.
Mix in the peas, tuna, celery and mayonnaise.
Season to taste.
Refrigerate 1 to 3 hours.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Simmer cider and spices 30 minutes. Turn off heat. Add rum and brandy. Serve while hot. Works well in crock-pot.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop the broccoli, cauliflower and onion. Toss well.
Mix the salt, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise. Pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix the condensed milk with the pineapple, nuts and coconut. Fold in the whipped topping mix, whipped according to instructions on the package.
Add the lemon juice.
Can be used in either a graham cracker crust or plain baked pastry.
Top with the same whipped topping mix (whipped).
Garnish with crushed nuts and pineapple, then refrigerate.

title: death by chocolate cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop 8 squares (1 package) of the chocolate; set aside.
Microwave remaining 8 squares chocolate in large microwavable bowl on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is melted and smooth.
Stir in sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Stir in reserved chopped chocolate and nuts.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 13 minutes or until cookies are puffed and feel set to the touch.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute. Transfer to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: amish acres bean soup
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in pan.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Melt bacon drippings in skillet.
Add vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper; mix well.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes, or until cabbage is tender but crisp, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: berry pie(can use any berry desired)
directions: Sift flour and sugar into bowl.
With pastry blender or fork, cut in butter.
Mix until it resembles corn meal.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Press pastry into a greased pie pan until firm on bottom and sides.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
Meanwhile, cook 1 cup of berries and water-cornstarch mixture until thick.
Place 3 cups of fresh berries in baked crust and pour the thickened berry mixture over the fresh fruit while still hot.

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry bacon in large saucepan until crisp and golden; remove from pan.
Add garlic and onion; saute for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients, except cod and evaporated milk.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add fish, cook 10 minutes more; stir occasionally.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Heat just to boiling.
Remove bay leaf and cloves before serving.
Garnish with crisp bacon.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for 3 hours.
Pinch off about 2 teaspoons of dough and roll into a ball with hands.
Press with glass dipped in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Stir in the package of taco seasoning. Add 3 to 4 tablespoons water.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Pour on the taco sauce.
Pour on the salsa.
Put the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve over shredded lettuce and nachos. Top with sour cream.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Brown stuffing crumbs in butter or margarine and spread 3/4 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together, including herb packet and spread on crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Very hearty!

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Spread generous amount of mayonnaise over this.
Grate cheese on top.
Put 7 pieces of bacon, cooked and crumbled, over cheese. Chill.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown your dry rice in the oil.
Watch closely and stir often because this doesn't take long.
After rice is brown, add the tomato sauce, water, pepper, onion and spices. Reduce heat and allow to come to a boil.
When it begins to boil, cover the pan and let it boil until rice fluffs with a fork.

title: low-fat macaroni salad
directions: Rinse macaroni in cold water and drain.
Add chopped vegetables to macaroni.
Pour fat-free Italian dressing in macaroni.
(May use more or less for your own desired taste.)
Add seasoning to taste.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Scald tomatoes, peel and scoop out insides, leaving a thick shell.
Turn upside down to drain.
Chop removed pulp and set aside.
Saute green pepper, green onions and celery in butter until tender but not browned.
Add reserved tomato pulp and cracker crumbs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fill tomatoes with mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: powder sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar and egg.
Then add other ingredients. Chill for 1 hour.
Put into cookie press. Press cookies onto cookie sheet. Bake until light brown.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: turkey-rice salad
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Add rice, peas and salt.
Stir to moisten.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Add mayonnaise, relish and onion.
Fold to blend.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Fold in turkey and cheese.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: strawberry fresh pie
directions: Combine pudding, gelatin, water and lemon juice in a saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Pour into a bowl and chill until thickened. Fold in topping, blending well.
Stir in berries. Pour into pie shell and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Partially thaw lemonade. Blend in milk and Cool Whip.
Blend well 2 to 3 minutes. Pour into baked shell. Let set 1 to 2 hours. Keep refrigerated.

title: blair and jasmine's favorite dinner
directions: Mix the ingredients and serve to the cats in two separate bowls, at room temperature.
Because the cats are smarter than dogs, I usually omit the dry cat food, because the cats tend to spit it out anyway and only eat the meat.
If you do include the cat food, you can pick it up from the rug and throw it to the birds later.

title: pickled mostaccioli
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add to cooked mostaccioli.
Stir often and let set.
Has better flavor if set overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken in as little water as possible with bouillon cube. Chop celery and pecans to your taste and add 1/2 c. broth from chicken. After chicken is cooked dice it and add the celery and pecans. Add Hellmann mayonnaise to taste. Boiled eggs can also be added.

title: glumpky soup
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add milk to make a thick consistency. Drop by spoonfuls into hot broth.
Dip the spoon in the hot broth each time.
Cook until done, about 5 to 10 minutes.
An easy soup, especially for fussy eaters.
An old family recipe.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Make into small rolls.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. While hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: spaghetti with white clam sauce
directions: Use fresh herbs if you have them.
Heat olive oil in large, deep pan.
Add the garlic, onion, celery and pepper to oil.
Stir until vegetables are soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Add 6 large scrubbed clams.
Lower heat and cover for 8 minutes or until clams open.
Remove clams and mince the meat.
Add minced clams to broth just before serving.
Serve over thin spaghetti.
Sprinkle with fresh ground black pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Be sure to have lots of garlic bread to dip in your broth.

title: 60 minute manicotti
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add 1 can mushrooms and jar of sauce. Simmer while preparing following.
Cook manicotti noodles according to directions.
When done, fill with ingredients.
Mix together eggs, cheese, cottage cheese, Parmesan, soft oleo, salt and pepper.
Stuff in shells.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Cook and stir ground beef until brown, drain.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion and set aside.
Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms.
Pat dough in an 8 x 8 x 2 greased baking pan pressing the dough 1/2 inch up the sides. Layer beef, tomatoes and green peppers on top of the dough.
Spoon sour cream mixture over top.
Sprinkle with Paprika if desired.
Bake until edges of dough are light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in 1/3.
Layer on bottom of cake pan (use 5 Twinkies).
Pour pudding over layer of Twinkies.
Place strawberries over pudding (you can use fresh strawberries).
Put another layer Twinkies.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans.

title: my favorite pie crust
directions: Pour hot water over lard; stir until smooth.
Add salt and flour until dough comes off easy.
Makes 6 crusts.

title: mother's chow mein
directions: Brown meat until done. Add peppers, onions, and celery cut into chunks. Cook until turning yellow. Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts, and bamboo sprouts. cook until all is hot! Mix water, flour, and soy sauce well. Add to meat while stirring to thicken. Serve over heated chow mein noodles. May add soy sauce to taste.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: If you can't make it out to the campfire, here's a favorite food brought indoors.
Take one graham cracker.
Add a jumbo marshmallow.
Top it with a piece of chocolate.
Melt the marshmallow and chocolate slightly in the microwave.
Top it with another graham cracker.

title: "taters"
directions: Saute the chopped onion in the butter in a large skillet until the onion is soft.
Add the soup and sour cream.
Fold in potatoes.
Place in a casserole.
Cover with the cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and bake in foil at 325° for 2 hours. Remove chicken from bones and cut into large chunks.
Slice tortillas in 1-inch strips.
Combine liquids and onion.
Layer in flat baking dish, ending with cheese.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. This is best if it stands 2 to 3 hours or overnight before baking.
Can be prepared and frozen for later.

title: holly candy
directions: Combine marshmallows, margarine, vanilla and green food coloring in top of a double boiler.
Stir constantly until marshmallows are melted.
Blend in cornflakes gradually (a cup at a time).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Decorate each one with 3 "red hots" cinnamon candies (for berries).

title: kansas city fruitcake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail.
Put nuts and brown sugar on top.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: easter egg braid
directions: Combine water, 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast in small bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and chop cherries.
In large bowl, combine milk, salt, shortening, egg and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add about half the flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in yeast and cherries.
Add flour gradually to form a very stiff dough.
Turn dough onto a heavily floured board and knead until smooth and no longer sticky. Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.

title: christmas boil(for simmering pots)
directions: Combine all ingredients except water and refrigerate in sealable bags.
Add water at time of use.
Refrigerate between uses.
Keeps several months.
Makes 2 batches; share half with a friend!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and layer with sliced bananas and wafers.
Chill and serve.,

title: pearls 'n chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt. Set aside.
Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in white chocolate and nuts, if desired.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes until edges are lightly browned.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: honeydew fruit boats
directions: Step 1:
Peel off all green portion of outer rind and all red melon, leaving only the white rind.
Cut in strips about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Measure in quarts.
Soak in cold salt water about 6 hours or overnight.
For salt solution, use 1/2 cup salt to 1 gallon of water.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a large pan.
Saute onion until lightly browned.
Add ground chuck and cook until beef is no longer pink. Add mushroom and tomato soups.
Add water and uncooked noodles. Cook until noodles are slightly tender.

title: graham cracker blueberry cake
directions: Roll graham crackers into crumbs.
Mix with margarine.
Pack in a shallow baking dish.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and eggs. Pour over crackers.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and spread with blueberry pie filling.
Whip 1 cup cream and spread over blueberries.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Chill for 12 hours or more before serving.

title: mom's homemade applesauce
directions: Cut apples into quarters; remove core, seeds and stem, but leave the peelings on.
Put into a large pot with just enough water to keep from burning.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until apples are soft.
Remove from heat.
Use food mill or large strainer to mash up the apples and separate the peelings.
Add sugar and cinnamon until it taste delicious and is a nice reddish-brown color.

title: sweet onion salad dressing
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together in blender; liquid first (onion slightly chopped), then add Wesson oil and white vinegar. Blend until smooth and creamy.

title: red fruit punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients in order given; pour in a regular Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine the ingredients and chill.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and oil until dissolved.
Pour over first mixture while hot.
Serve cold.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and salt (taste, it should be sweet and salty, you could add a little more of either as needed).
Add oil.
Add flour as needed until dough an be put on a board and worked.
(Keep flour at a minimum, dough should be soft, never make it too stiff.) Let rise until double in bulk (should do in about 1 1/2 hours).
Work down.
Roll out and cut. Put in an oiled pan and let rise for 20 minuets to 1/2 hour.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: taco bowls #2
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
On baking sheet, place 6 balls of foil (4 inches diameter).
Spray 10-inch nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Over high heat, heat 1 flour tortilla 5 seconds on each side until tortilla is softened.
Drain on paper towels.
Immediately drape tortilla over foil ball on baking sheet.
Repeat with additional tortillas.
Bake 5 minutes or until golden.
Remove from oven and cool on foil.
Fill as desired.

title: light creamy cake
directions: Mix well; spoon batter into prepared 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Best with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the flour and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix the oleo, cocoa and water together in a saucepan.
Bring this mixture to a rapid boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add the soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, mayonnaise and onion.
Pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted mayonnaise over crumbs.
Bake at 400° until done or crackers are golden brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: 1. Crush the oreos to look like potting soil.

title: chicken pecan quiche
directions: Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in bowl; stir in oil. Set aside 1/4 mixture.
Press remaining mixture in bottom and up sides of 9-inch quiche dish.
Prick bottom and sides with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave french onion soup
directions: In a 3-quart casserole combine onion and butter or margarine. Cook, covered, on High (100%) for 8 to 11 minutes or until onions are tender, stirring after half the cooking time.
Stir in beef broth and hot water.
Cover, cook on High (100%) for 4 to 6 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Ladle soup into 4 large individual bowls or casseroles.
Top with bread slices. Sprinkle evenly with cheeses.
Cook on Medium-high (70%) for 3 to 5 minutes, or until cheese melts, rearranging bowls once or twice. Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed prunes
directions: Soak the prunes in hot water and cover until soft.
Cut the prunes in half and fill with cream cheese.
Great with roast tenderloin.

title: buckeye pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Divide and spread into 2 graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate or freeze to set.
Beat pudding and milk 1 minute on low speed.
Divide and pour on top of peanut butter mixture in each pie.
Garnish with dollops of Cool Whip and chocolate sprinkles.
Refrigerate.

title: mom's wesson oil cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs with fork until well blended. Stir in oil.
Stir in extracts.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Add flour.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
(These cookies will spread.)
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: steak and mushroom gravy
directions: In skillet, brown meat on both sides.
Pour water into skillet.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender and most of the water has evaporated.
Pour soup over meat and stir until soup comes to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk, pineapple and juice and bread cubes.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good with chicken or ham.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Mix sugar and water
until
dissolved.
Add
juice
and mashed bananas.
Freeze in large
container (can make ahead of time). Thaw 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Mix up to 6 bottles of ginger ale.
Punch should be slushy.

title: mushroom logs
directions: Separate crescent roll dough into 8 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal to cover bottom of cookie sheet.
Combine cream cheese, mushrooms and salt, mixing well.
Spread mixture over dough.
Roll up in a jelly roll fashion.
Pinch seams to seal. Slice logs into 1 inch pieces; place seam side down on ungreased baking sheet. Brush each log with beaten egg and sprinkle poppy seeds.
Bake 375 for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pickled bean salad
directions: Drain the beans well; toss in a bowl with the sliced onion and celery.
Mix vinegar, salad oil, sugar and salt well.
Pour over the bean mixture; mix well.
Place in airtight container; refrigerate overnight.
This salad keeps well for at least a week.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Combine flour and seasonings; coat chops with mixture.
Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese in small bowl.
Dip chops in egg, then crumb mixture.
Brown chops slowly in hot oil in skillet. Place slice of Mozzarella cheese over each chop.
Pour sauce over cheese; sprinkle with oregano.
Cover.
Simmer for 50 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour, then broth and milk.
Stir constantly until thickens and smooth.
Add drained onions and seasoning.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cover with crumbs and cheese.

title: apricot jello dessert
directions: Bring pineapple, juice and Jell-O to boil; set aside to cool. Add buttermilk and 1 Cool Whip.
Set in refrigerator to set, then top with other Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts over top.

title: butter frosting
directions: Put butter in bowl and beat with mixed until fluffy.
Add 2 cups of the powdered sugar, then beat in the 1/4 c. milk and vanilla.
Add remaining sugar and mix until smooth and fluffy.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Place 1 package of crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread in pan.
Put second package of crescent rolls on top.
Melt butter; pour on top and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put all together and mix well with rotary beater.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake slowly about 1 hour at 300°.
Serve with or without whipped cream.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Mix with spoon until thoroughly mixed.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese ginger frosting
directions: In a small bowl, and with the electric mixer beat together the cream cheese, butter or margarine and the vanilla.
Gradually add the powdered sugar and the ground ginger.
Continue beating until the frosting has a smooth consistency.
Spread on cooled Pineapple Cake.

title: dirty rice casserolegroves, texas
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: peach and berry kanten
directions: Arrange fruit in a mold or bowl.
Add juice, salt and agar in a saucepan.
Bring to a light boil.
Stir occasionally for 5 to 8 minutes, or until agar is dissolved.
Pour over fruit.
Cool or chill 1 to 2 hours, uncovered, until firm.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate mixture for several hours.
Just before serving, whip 1 pint (or less) of cream.
Fold into fruit-nut mixture and serve.

title: yellow squash puff
directions: Mix all together and drop in hot oil with a teaspoon.
When brown, drain on paper towel.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Divide broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Dice the onion. Place all salad ingredients in a bowl and toss to mix.

title: creamy pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Drain hot pepper rings and add to noodles along with rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Noodles can be warm or cold while mixing.
Serve salad chilled.

title: millet crumble
directions: Add millet
to
boiling
water.
Reduce heat and simmer approximately 1 hour.
Blend creamy half of the millet, juice, vanilla and
salt.
Pour into bowl and blend other half.
Stir together in bowl.

title: white delight
directions: Melt almond bark in
Microwave and stir all other ingredients in melted chocolate until coated.

title: portuguese kale soup
directions: Place kidney beans, chourico and
chicken in a large pot; cover with water.
Add salt and simmer until almost cooked.
Add kale, the potatoes and the macaroni and cook until done.
Add a paste of 1/4 cup flour and water to soup and cook about 5 minutes longer adjust seasoning to taste.

title: egg boats
directions: Peel eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Put yolks in a small bowl with the mayonnaise and mash with a fork.
Add salt and pepper if you wish.
Spoon egg yolk mixture onto egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve chilled.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Drain strawberries and save juice to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Mix with jello and beat until jello dissolves.
Take off stove and add ice cream.
Refrigerate about 45 minutes; then add strawberries and pour into shell.

title: jezebel dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: delicious applesauce cake(makes large cake)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and applesauce.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add to the first mixture and beat well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours. (Check for doneness.)

title: speedy spinach
directions: Thaw and drain spinach; mix with onion soup mix and sour cream.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken stir-fry(method:  skillet)
directions: Put 2 tablespoons oil in pan.
Heat; cook chicken about 2 minutes, stirring often.
Remove chicken.
Add remaining oil and carrots, onions, mushrooms, garlic and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry until carrots are tender (2 minutes).
Add chicken, soy sauce and broccoli; stir-fry until broccoli is tender, about 1 minute.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine raisins, nuts and apples in a large bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, spices and salt.
Add beaten egg, melted butter, baking soda, dissolved in juice to fruit and flour mixture.

title: company casserole
directions: Fry onion in oil in large skillet.
Add beef, salt and pepper. Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce.
Remove from heat, cook spaghetti until done and drain.
Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green pepper and green onion.

title: fruit stack cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg and mix well. Add molasses and mix.
Add half of buttermilk and mix.
Add dry ingredients alternately with rest of the buttermilk.
Mix well. Grease and flour 9-inch cake pans.
Pour 1 cup of batter into each pan.
Spread to sides of pans.
This will make 9 to 10 layers. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Cool layers on towel.
Put sweetened applesauce between each layer or use dried apple filling.

title: reuben turnovers
directions: Separate rolls into 8 rectangles on ungreased baking sheet, pressing perforations to seal.
Layer equal portions
of corned beef, sauerkraut and cheese in center of each rectangle.
Top evenly with dressing.
Moisten edges with water and fold dough in half, pressing edges with a fork to seal.
Brush tops with butter and sprinkle lightly with poppy seed.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: crispix party mix
directions: Combine cereal, nuts and pretzels in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
Stir together the remaining ingredients.
Gently stir spices and margarine into cereal mixture until evenly coated. Bake at
250° for about 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container. Yield: 9 cups.

title: orange molded salad
directions: Dissolve
gelatin in boiling orange juice.
Immediately add sherbet and stir until melted.
Partially chill.
Add Cool Whip and Mandarin oranges.
Return to refrigerator to set.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat the marshmallow cream and cream cheese together and add nutmeg and cinnamon.
Delicious dip for cut up fresh fruit.

title: marmalade bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Reserve 1/4 cup marmalade. Combine remaining 1 1/4 cups marmalade, egg, orange juice and oil. Add to flour mixture, stirring until moistened.
Stir in nuts. Turn into a greased 9 1/2 x
x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Remove from pan and place on baking sheet. Spread top with reserved marmalade and return to oven 1 minute to glaze.
Cool.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Put in bowl and add butter. Mix until smooth and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350 F for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add chili seasoning mix and drained kidney beans to the hamburger.
Stir and heat.
Make salad with diced lettuce, tomatoes, onions and pepper.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Brush a little egg white on unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° about 1 minute.
This prevents a soggy crust.
Beat eggs lightly; add other ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, 15 minutes at 375° and 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add olives.
Divide meat mixture into 8 portions and place on tortillas.
Place 1/4 c. cheese on top and roll up tortilla.
In a large skillet, mix soup, milk, chilies and garlic powder.
Lay tortillas in sauce and top with remaining cheese.
Heat until cheese starts to melt.

title: southwest salad
directions: Place greens in large salad bowl. Add corn, beans, olives, and chicken strips. Combine Ranch dressing and Picante sauce. Prepare individual servings; top with broken chips, cheese, and diced tomatoes. Spoon dressing over individual servings. Serve immediately.

title: white buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add a little buttermilk and beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with the rest of the buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in three 9-inch layer pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Warm 3 cups milk slowly and add sugar and chocolate.
Mix together 1/2 cup cold milk with cornstarch.
Add this to chocolate, sugar and milk.
Add vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Top with meringue made from 2 egg whites. Brown in oven.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender and pour.

title: berry butter
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add berries and sugar.
After ingredients are heated and blended, the sauce may be poured over ice cream, pound cake, pancakes or waffles.

title: mom staub's potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients quickly as the potatoes will darken.
Drop on hot greased griddle.
Fry until golden brown and potatoes are tender.
Serve with butter, syrup, jelly or applesauce.

title: preacher's roast
directions: Brown roast and then cup aluminum foil up around meat.
Add soup and 1 to 2 quarts of water, according to size of roast.
Cover the roast thoroughly, rubbing into the surface of the meat the mixture of ingredients.
Wrap with heavy duty aluminum foil. Puncture top of foil with table fork several times.
Place roast in pan.
Place this into a water-filled larger pan on top of 2 bricks to keep roast from direct heat.
Cook on gas grill 4 to 5 hours with cover closed.
Be sure to keep water in bottom of pan.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oven dressing
directions: Cook ground
meat slightly until it changes color.
Add all ingredients to
ground meat; mix well and pour into 12 x 9 x 2-inch
pan.
Seal	real
tight
with
heavy foil.	Place in preheated oven and cook for one hour at 400° or one and a half hours at 350°.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix and set aside to cool.

title: camp fire stew
directions: Brown beef and onion in a 4-quart pan.
Drain.
Add the other ingredients except lemon, spaghetti and sour cream.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add spaghetti and simmer 15 minutes more or until spaghetti is ready.

title: the best cake ever
directions: Mix all ingredients into cake mix.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Grease loaf pan.
Makes 1 loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beefy chili mac(30 minutes)
directions: Cut beef steaks lengthwise into 1-inch strips, then crosswise into 1-inch pieces.
Spray Dutch oven with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat oven medium high heat until hot.
Add beef and onion to pan; cook and stir 3 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing for a crowd
directions: In large bowl, crumble cornbread with dry stuffing mix.

Add remaining ingredients and seasonings with enough broth to hold mixture together. (It should be moist, but not runny.) Grease 2 or more shallow baking pans or cookie sheets. With measuring cup or scoop, mound about 1/2 cup mixture on baking sheet as for cookies. Flatten each patty slightly. Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.
Remove patties to platter and serve with chicken/turkey and gravy.

title: play dough
directions: In heavy aluminum saucepan, mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes on medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Immediately knead slightly. Store in airtight container.

Will keep for several weeks.
